name: Gorgeous Eco-Friendly Home in Green Lake
description: Prime location! Explore the active, dog friendly Green Lake area filled with a variety of eateries, coffee shops, boutiques, an expansive park and year round events.  Stay right in the heart of this family friendly walker’s paradise,  surrounded by lush greenery and endless recreation.  Less than two blocks from the lake front park and a 2.8 mile loop trail, welcoming folks of all ages and abilities, and their dogs!   Hearthstone Retirement Community is also a short walk from the house.
neighborhood_overview:
The Green Lake neighborhood is located about 15 minutes North of Downtown Seattle.
A proud community of inviting local flair boasts an array of cafe's, coffee shops, fine restaurants, retail shopping, wellness services and other public conveniences.

Green Lake Park has a year round 2.8 mile waterfront walking trail and a 3.1 mile outer perimeter trail.
Non motorized water activities such as paddle boards and kayaks are permitted on the lake.
The park also has ball fields, sport courts, a designated shallow swimming area for children and a serene setting for picnics. And it's dog friendly!

Woodland Park Zoo is located nearby as well.

neighborhood_overview:
Welcome to the vibrant neighborhood of Capitol Hill in Seattle. Situated just a stone's throw away from Broadway Street and Volunteer Park, this area offers a dynamic and eclectic experience for visitors.

Capitol Hill is known for its lively atmosphere, diverse community, and rich cultural scene. It is a hub for arts, music, dining, and nightlife, making it a popular destination for locals and tourists alike.

Broadway Street, the main thoroughfare of Capitol Hill, is a bustling and vibrant stretch lined with an array of shops, boutiques, restaurants, cafes, and bars. You'll find a wide variety of cuisines, from trendy eateries to cozy coffee shops, offering everything from international flavors to local favorites. Take a leisurely stroll down Broadway, indulge in some retail therapy, savor delicious food, and immerse yourself in the lively energy of the neighborhood.

Nestled within Capitol Hill, Volunteer Park provides a peaceful and picturesque oasis.

description: Show up and start living from day one in Seattle with this cozy one bedroom Blueground apartment. You’ll love coming home to this thoughtfully furnished, beautifully designed, and fully-equipped Lower Queen Anne home with stunning views over the city. (ID #SEA579)
neighborhood_overview: This furnished apartment is located in Lower Queen Anne, an up and coming neighborhood around the Seattle Center. The area is also referred to as Uptown by locals, especially in recent years. The Space Needle is just a few minutes' walk from Lower Queen Anne, as are the Pacific Northwest Ballet, the Seattle Children's Theatre, and the Museum of Pop Culture. The neighborhood is also home to the headquarters of the Seattle Post-Intelligencer as well as a thriving dining scene. You can find everything from fast-casual spots like local favorite Dick's Drive-in -- the Lower Queen Anne is the only Dick's location with seating -- to high-end, white tablecloth restaurants. Lower Queen Anne is connected to downtown by the Seattle Center monorail, and several bus lines serve the neighborhood.
host_about:
We’re Blueground, a global proptech company with several thousand move-in-ready apartments in a growing number of major cities around the world. With flexible terms and homes in vibrant, centrally based neighborhoods, you’ll feel at home and free to roam for as long as you want — a month, a year, or longer. 

Each apartment is thoughtfully designed with exclusive furnishings, fully equipped kitchens, and incredible amenities – making every day a five-star experience. From day one, you’ll enjoy high-speed Wi-Fi, premium linens, and smart home entertainment. Plus, access to pools, gyms, and outdoor spaces in select buildings.

Why stress over your apartment? We provide a hassle-free alternative — a consistent, quality guest experience that starts even before you arrive. Because we let you book our most up-to-date apartment listings online, confirm with a click, pay securely, and check in easily. 

Even better? You can enhance your stay with car rentals, grocery delivery, laundry services, and more through our special partnerships. 

During your stay
Upon arrival, you’ll either be greeted personally by a Blueground team member or given self-check-in instructions. The entire apartment is yours! You’ll enjoy reliable support via email, phone, and our Guest App, where you can request everything from a home cleaning to extra towels. 

We’ll share all details upon confirmation of your stay.

neighborhood_overview:
Pigeon Point is our friendly and diverse little neighborhood, a secluded urban oasis perched high above the bustle of Delridge Way. A short walk around the neighborhood offers spectacular views of the downtown skyline and Elliott Bay, a big playfield at the local school, and running trails through the largest protected greenbelt in the city.

A couple of short blocks down the hill on Delridge you will find convenient groceries at Delridge Deli Mart (open until midnight), board games at Uptown Espresso, craft beer/cider and rotating food trucks at Ounces Taproom & Beer Garden, and live music/trivia/great brunch at Skylark Cafe & Club. There is a Subway too if you're looking for a quick bite. West Seattle Health Club is within a half mile and offers a 5-day free pass.

Venture further and find some of the many reasons we chose to live in West Seattle: shopping on California Ave, restaurants, bars, old growth forest parks, Alki Beach, a great 18-hole golf course, and
host_about:
We're Christa and Brian, a young active couple with two friendly cats (Hank and Steve). You'll find that we're friendly, socially conscious, and easy-going. We like to enjoy the outdoors as well as a drink on the deck or watching sports/movies. We're big fans of the Seahawks  and Mariners as well as our alma maters, Gonzaga and UW. Feel free to pull up a seat and join us if we're watching a game during your stay!

We love to meet new people and help them have great experiences in our wonderful city, although we are happy to interact with our guests as much or as little as they desire. Our work schedules are pretty flexible which allows us to help our guests get settled and provide local travel advice. We look forward to welcoming you into our home!

name: New Orleans room
description:
Nola room is a simple cozy room with a comfy bed, mini fridge, bathrobes, towels , clean linens and fresh water. Come enjoy easy access to all the stadiums , T Mobile arena , climate pledge arena, downtown, pike place market and points beyond.. within 15-20 min
We are in a lively fun neighborhood but please note its NOT a quiet area as we are by an airport and hopping restaurants. This is a historic hotel with artsy flair. Your room is private. Three bathrooms and full kitchen are shared.
host_about:
I am a visual artist who is  the  director of a community  Arts Center, art studios and guest rooms co-mingle to create a fun experience if you choose. Original art lines the hallways and some of the rooms  of our space, which is a restored Hotel and we welcome all including non artists with open arms. Not Arty at all? that's ok we are also close to stadiums, downtown,  nature  (Kubota Gardens, the arboretum, Seward Park, Alki Beach, Lincoln Park, Schmitz Park,  and yep golfing options (West Seattle and Jefferson Park both have awesome courses). We are also located up the street from the Boeing Flight museum and school , Northwest Institute of Asian and Oriental medicine (NIAOM) and also   The School of Acrobatics and Circus arts (SANCA) and not far away from Fed Ex and Amazon downtown.

Are you a foodie ???
We have soooo many amazing restaurants in the area (South Park, Georgetown  Beacon hill and White Center ) of course down town also but if you want to spread the  love in the neighborhood then just look at my guide book (south Seattle's finest)  

Our Space
---------------
Our space is hard to describe but we have been compared to a scrappy McMenamin's We have a large space but very clean and magical ( built as a hotel in 1904) our historical building has been lovingly restored .
We are not your usual space so please read carefully... think old school hotel / European hostel without the ghosts....or maybe there are ghosts you will have to see (wink wink) No ghosts that  are too precocious I promise :)
We have three shared and very clean bathrooms
One very well stocked kitchen (pots, pans, dishes and the like provided) 
And if you enjoy a morning coffee or tea / or evening glass of wine (or smoke) we have a very expansive back porch with couches , tables and a designated smoking area (New Orleans meets Georgetown)

 If you are sick please do not travel.  I'm a fairly warm person, i like to give hugs but currently I am keeping social distancing and ask that if you visit us that you do also.  
About Me 
I LOVE LOVE LOVE being a host, traveling and meeting awesome people. I have recently adopted a little girl doggie named Pickles who is sweet and learning how to greet people, she came all the way from Mexico but is not traumatized at all, if you are allergic to dogs then please let me know before hand so i can have her in my office.   
 The building is truly a magical charmer and  I think you will enjoy your stay here

Special things to be aware of
* I follow Airbnb’s enhanced cleaning protocol, which was developed with expert guidance.


***Please note that the rooms are on the second floor and we unfortunately are not ADA accesible. 

***Also of note our space is in the city so it's active and not always cricket quiet some noise from events , street or airplanes may happen, if you need a super quiet space book a hotel in the country. Most of the time the building itself is quiet but we have planes that fly overhead and a hopping building with fun restaurants and a pool hall downstairs. 

HANDS ON / only one staff member / so please be communicative
 I only have one staff member and do all cleaning, booking and greeting (except evening arrivals) myself so it is appreciated that you let me know your arrival time (as close as possible) at the time of your booking request and communicate this when you book if possible. I greet you in person or our evening manager if your arrival is after 6 pm 
***After 10 pm arrivals \late arrivals will require a $20 hr surcharge**. Late arrivals  with prior arrangement may be accepted) please inform me of your arrival time at the time of your booking request. Of course we know that emergencies happen ( delayed flights are real) and will work with you to make sure you are safe and respected

About ME
   I am an artist , entrepreneur and lover of people, plants and four legged beings. Sadly we can not allow animals in the rooms at this time unless they are a documented service animal with a vets authorization (must provide before booking)
   I  easy going person and  always try to keep our space filled with good energy. We welcome all respectful people here, this is a safe space. 
* please be vaccinated so we may keep everyone safe. Currently we are not requiring masking or social distancing in shared spaces , but you may do what ever makes you comfortable and please if you are immunocompromised just let us know and we will also wear our masks for you. Just let us know.


WANT TO GET MARRIED WHILE YOUR HERE?
  Well we have a wedding chapel on our property called Shotgun ceremonies
 ( you can find online) if ya wanna get hitched while your here. :) 
The lovely officiant of Shotgun ceremonies can work with you on a wedding package ( and yes Elvis can be present ) believe it!!
( I am not  the officiant...so please do not ask me about setting up the details ) but if you book thru her then you can also organize your guests rooms with me,
If you organize  / coordinate  to rent ALL the rooms in our space (There are 8 room), I will give you a 10% off the total (one point of contact only please for simplicity)  
****Please no non Airbnb guests onsite unless they are helping you with your luggage , or help up and down stairs

****NO SMOKING of anything inside BUILDING / NO VAPING/
 …you can do all these things in our Smoking area outside. I  am easily accessible if you need anything, I am happy to oblige most requests and strive to make every traveler feel welcome  but I also will give you your space. I try to take Sundays off to rest and have time with my dog. (Dog lives off site )
I am also happy to  help you plan a fun day here in Seattle.  I have allot of travel info and happy to give you any recommendations . 


We look forward to meeting you and making your stay awesome!

To earn more about our community of Just search Georgetown Seattle
My life motto
"Life is short, art is long"

neighborhood_overview:
Capital Hill is undeniably the Seattle's current coolest 'hood. It’s home to the city’s musicians and artists, counterculture mavens, and (for better or worse) flocks of yuppies attracted to the neighborhood’s unique spirit -- especially the dozens of bars, restaurants, music venues, and theaters that dot its landscape.

If you’re visiting Capitol Hill for the first time, it can be overwhelming, because there is so much to do. Capitol Hill is one of Seattle’s most popular neighborhoods. A hotspot of nightlife and restaurants, and the center of Seattle’s vibrant variety of independent shops, including one of the city’s largest bookstores. Just a few blocks north of the retail area, residents can find houses ranging from modest to grand. Capitol Hill has easy access to downtown as well as points north and south thanks to a light rail station in the heart of the neighborhood. For something quieter, residents can visit Cal Anderson Park, Volunteer Park, or one of the many area g

neighborhood_overview:
The home is located in the charming Judkins Park district of Seattle, surrounded by vibrant, evolving neighborhoods. This area maintains a peaceful vibe, centered around Judkins Park itself—a spacious green escape within the city.

Judkins Park is known for its mix of older single-family homes, newer townhomes, and apartment buildings, with most dining and commerce located along its edges. Green spaces abound, including Judkins Park, which parallels 23rd Ave, and Sam Smith Park, located over the I-90 tunnel and next to the Northwest African American Museum.

Well-connected by public transit, Judkins Park offers easy access to downtown, the Mount Baker Light Rail Station, and nearby neighborhoods, such as the International District. This makes it a prime location for both commuters and those eager to explore Seattle’s diverse communities
host_about:
Hi, I'm Crystal!

In 2016 I took the road trip of a lifetime intending to move from St. Louis to San Fransico. While on a pitstop in Seattle, I stayed in an AirBNB where the host said he just left San Fransico because Seattle was better. After that conversation my road trip ended early. I took his word and ended up renting a 1 bed/1 bath in Seattle. I enjoyed my AirBNB experience so much I listed my personal apartment. Since 2016 I've rented out 3 more of my personal spaces and have helped others list their own spaces. I love styling homes and creating a fun and unique experience for guests. I hope all my guests come to fall in love with Seattle, just as I did.

description:

You will be close to all the action!

neighborhood_overview: Westlake is Seattle's smallest neighborhood located on the western shore of Lake Union. Our house is located on a quiet street off of Dexter Avenue and there are two sets of stairs that will lead you down to Westlake Avenue and the lakefront. Just steps away on Dexter you can find several local businesses. Lyon's Grocery is an excellent convenience store with delicious deli sandwiches. If you like boba, Tea King is a great option. The Toledo is a unique bar that also serves amazing flatbreads. And of course there's the Swedish Club which hosts various events throughout the week. If you enjoy kayaking or stand up paddle boarding, I would recommend the Northwest Outdoor Center.

host_about:
I am a visual artist who is  the  director of a community  Arts Center, art studios and guest rooms co-mingle to create a fun experience if you choose. Original art lines the hallways and some of the rooms  of our space, which is a restored Hotel and we welcome all including non artists with open arms. Not Arty at all? that's ok we are also close to stadiums, downtown,  nature  (Kubota Gardens, the arboretum, Seward Park, Alki Beach, Lincoln Park, Schmitz Park,  and yep golfing options (West Seattle and Jefferson Park both have awesome courses). We are also located up the street from the Boeing Flight museum and school , Northwest Institute of Asian and Oriental medicine (NIAOM) and also   The School of Acrobatics and Circus arts (SANCA) and not far away from Fed Ex and Amazon downtown.

Are you a foodie ???
We have soooo many amazing restaurants in the area (South Park, Georgetown  Beacon hill and White Center ) of course down town also but if you want to spread the  love in the neighborhood then just look at my guide book (south Seattle's finest)  

Our Space
---------------
Our space is hard to describe but we have been compared to a scrappy McMenamin's We have a large space but very clean and magical ( built as a hotel in 1904) our historical building has been lovingly restored .
We are not your usual space so please read carefully... think old school hotel / European hostel without the ghosts....or maybe there are ghosts you will have to see (wink wink) No ghosts that  are too precocious I promise :)
We have three shared and very clean bathrooms
One very well stocked kitchen (pots, pans, dishes and the like provided) 
And if you enjoy a morning coffee or tea / or evening glass of wine (or smoke) we have a very expansive back porch with couches , tables and a designated smoking area (New Orleans meets Georgetown)

 If you are sick please do not travel.  I'm a fairly warm person, i like to give hugs but currently I am keeping social distancing and ask that if you visit us that you do also.  
About Me 
I LOVE LOVE LOVE being a host, traveling and meeting awesome people. I have recently adopted a little girl doggie named Pickles who is sweet and learning how to greet people, she came all the way from Mexico but is not traumatized at all, if you are allergic to dogs then please let me know before hand so i can have her in my office.   
 The building is truly a magical charmer and  I think you will enjoy your stay here

Special things to be aware of
* I follow Airbnb’s enhanced cleaning protocol, which was developed with expert guidance.


***Please note that the rooms are on the second floor and we unfortunately are not ADA accesible. 

***Also of note our space is in the city so it's active and not always cricket quiet some noise from events , street or airplanes may happen, if you need a super quiet space book a hotel in the country. Most of the time the building itself is quiet but we have planes that fly overhead and a hopping building with fun restaurants and a pool hall downstairs. 

HANDS ON / only one staff member / so please be communicative
 I only have one staff member and do all cleaning, booking and greeting (except evening arrivals) myself so it is appreciated that you let me know your arrival time (as close as possible) at the time of your booking request and communicate this when you book if possible. I greet you in person or our evening manager if your arrival is after 6 pm 
***After 10 pm arrivals \late arrivals will require a $20 hr surcharge**. Late arrivals  with prior arrangement may be accepted) please inform me of your arrival time at the time of your booking request. Of course we know that emergencies happen ( delayed flights are real) and will work with you to make sure you are safe and respected

About ME
   I am an artist , entrepreneur and lover of people, plants and four legged beings. Sadly we can not allow animals in the rooms at this time unless they are a documented service animal with a vets authorization (must provide before booking)
   I  easy going person and  always try to keep our space filled with good energy. We welcome all respectful people here, this is a safe space. 
* please be vaccinated so we may keep everyone safe. Currently we are not requiring masking or social distancing in shared spaces , but you may do what ever makes you comfortable and please if you are immunocompromised just let us know and we will also wear our masks for you. Just let us know.


WANT TO GET MARRIED WHILE YOUR HERE?
  Well we have a wedding chapel on our property called Shotgun ceremonies
 ( you can find online) if ya wanna get hitched while your here. :) 
The lovely officiant of Shotgun ceremonies can work with you on a wedding package ( and yes Elvis can be present ) believe it!!
( I am not  the officiant...so please do not ask me about setting up the details ) but if you book thru her then you can also organize your guests rooms with me,
If you organize  / coordinate  to rent ALL the rooms in our space (There are 8 room), I will give you a 10% off the total (one point of contact only please for simplicity)  
****Please no non Airbnb guests onsite unless they are helping you with your luggage , or help up and down stairs

****NO SMOKING of anything inside BUILDING / NO VAPING/
 …you can do all these things in our Smoking area outside. I  am easily accessible if you need anything, I am happy to oblige most requests and strive to make every traveler feel welcome  but I also will give you your space. I try to take Sundays off to rest and have time with my dog. (Dog lives off site )
I am also happy to  help you plan a fun day here in Seattle.  I have allot of travel info and happy to give you any recommendations . 


We look forward to meeting you and making your stay awesome!

To earn more about our community of Just search Georgetown Seattle
My life motto
"Life is short, art is long"

name: Private Wedgwood Guesthouse
description:
Enjoy Seattle while staying in our private guesthouse!

We are the main residents of the property, and are excited to host you in our guest space while you explore the city.
neighborhood_overview:
While this house is technically located in the Wedgwood neighborhood, it closely borders the Maple Leaf, Roosevelt, and Ravenna neighborhoods, all which are relatively quiet communities, populated with more single family dwellings than apartment buildings.

You’ll be a short drive to all kinds of different local eateries and a variety of great parks, including Green Lake, which is a beautiful location to go for a walk and be outdoors while still being in the city!
host_about:
Hi there - 

We are the Blues! We are both CA natives, and moved up to Seattle for school and work. We love the PNW - the outdoors are at our fingertips here!

Laura works at the Seattle Children's Research Institute, supporting principal investigators at the Center for Developmental Biology and Regenerative Medicine. Josh is an architect designing educational architecture for schools throughout Seattle and the surrounding areas. When we're not working, we're either hiking, going to the movies, or hanging with our church community. 

We also LOVE to travel! Post graduation, Laura traveled for eleven months on a trip called the World Race, visiting a different country each month, doing various volunteer/service/mission work in each place. In that year we visited four continents, working in orphanages, teaching English, working in churches, clearing land, and connecting with communities all over the world! It certainly fueled a longing to explore, venture to new places, and experience new communities. But it has also grown an appreciation for a sense of "home" and comfort. Laura has visited 44 countries so far, and her dream would be to visit them all! 

We got married in April 2018, and spent our honeymoon in Chile - specifically the Patagonia region. When traveling, we're on the look out for the tastiest food spots, live music, best views, and any sort of fun, cultural events unique to that place. We hope to venture to many new places together. However, our newest adventure is hosting our very own Airbnb in partnership with the company, Loftium! 

We look forward to hosting you!

Cheers,
Laura and Josh

description: Discover the best of Seattle, with this two bedroom apartment in Ballard. with views over the city. neighborhood_overview: This furnished home is situated in Ballard, a hip waterfront neighborhood offering trendy restaurants, shops, breweries, and bars. Ships pass through the Locks, which have become a popular picnic spot. The beach at Golden Gardens Park offers mountain views and cater to sunbathers and volleyball players. There’s also a Nordic Heritage Museum here that displays the area’s Scandinavian roots. There are tons of ways to access the rest of the city from here, for instance, by monorail, streetcar, and bus.
host_about:
We’re Blueground, a global proptech company with several thousand move-in-ready apartments in a growing number of major cities around the world. With flexible terms and homes in vibrant, centrally based neighborhoods, you’ll feel at home and free to roam for as long as you want — a month, a year, or longer. 

Each apartment is thoughtfully designed with exclusive furnishings, fully equipped kitchens, and incredible amenities – making every day a five-star experience. From day one, you’ll enjoy high-speed Wi-Fi, premium linens, and smart home entertainment. Plus, access to pools, gyms, and outdoor spaces in select buildings.

Why stress over your apartment? We provide a hassle-free alternative — a consistent, quality guest experience that starts even before you arrive. Because we let you book our most up-to-date apartment listings online, confirm with a click, pay securely, and check in easily. 

Even better? You can enhance your stay with car rentals, grocery delivery, laundry services, and more through our special partnerships. 

During your stay
Upon arrival, you’ll either be greeted personally by a Blueground team member or given self-check-in instructions. The entire apartment is yours! You’ll enjoy reliable support via email, phone, and our Guest App, where you can request everything from a home cleaning to extra towels. 

We’ll share all details upon confirmation of your stay.

name: West Seattle Beachy Guest Suite
description: Welcome to West Seattle Beachy Guest Suite! Our guest house is located in a quiet hillside in Highland Park neighborhood of West Seattle. As a guest, you'll enjoy the cozy 2 bedroom (about 750 sq. ft), fully furnished basement apartment. A separate entrance from the main house allows you to come and go as you please, making it ideal for couples, solo adventurers, business travelers, and families with kids.
neighborhood_overview:
West Seattle is a great, family-friendly neighborhood in Seattle. There are a lot of amenities not too far away. Our location is called Highland Park (near Delridge Ave).

Our favorite seaside park, Lincoln Park is only 4 miles away, it's known for one of the nicest views of Puget Sound. West Seattle is also home to Alki Beach (an 8-10 minute drive from our place) and the popular Alaska Junction. Alaska Junction is filled with great stores and restaurants too, so you don't have to go too far away for a great meal.

We are 2 miles from Westwood Village, a shopping center with amenities such as a grocery store, banks, and other conveniences like Target, Marshalls, Starbucks, 24 Hour Fitness, restaurants & fast food. It’s a 2-minute drive or a 10-minute walk.

name: Heart of West Seattle / 9m drive to Alki Beach
description:
✿ Elegant room in a new modern home, located in a quiet, safe & charming neighborhood, steps away from the vibrant West Seattle Alaska Junction.
✿ We painted the walls, assembled furniture & carefully picked out every item to make a beautiful space for our guests to enjoy. It comes w high-speed wifi & free street parking.
✿ After a day of exploring nearby beaches w stunning sunsets, kayaking the Puget Sound, or eating your way through the Farmer’s Market, come home & unwind in your cozy room.
neighborhood_overview:
A WALKER'S PARADISE — CHARMING ✣ SAFE ✣ WALK TO EVERYTHING
✿ No car, no problem! One block away from the heart of one of Seattle's best neighborhoods (Alaska Junction), 4 min walk to public transit, the home has a 97 walk score making it a "Walker's Paradise".
✿ 9 min drive to Alki sandy beach w/ stunning sunsets & city skyline

Literally one block away from restaurants, bars, coffee shops, spa, yoga/gym, live music, bike shop (rent a bike & you're at Alki Beach in 5-10 min!)
Even better, four grocery stores within 5 minutes (Safeway, QFC, Whole Foods & Trader Joe’s) and lots of cute shops at your doorstep.

There is a Farmer’s market every Sunday, just a block away on California Ave. It is a wonderful opportunity to purchase delicious local treats and goods. Additionally, there is an art walk every 2nd Thursday of the month.
host_about:
Our guest rooms were made with love and care. We painted the walls, assembled furniture, and carefully picked out every item ourselves to make a beautiful space for our guests to enjoy. 

Mindfulness is our core value and we brought that practice to the whole process of setting up the rooms. We chose materials that are eco-friendly and free of harmful chemicals. We are thoughtful about our impact on our guests' health and safety, our neighbors, our environment, and the city of Seattle. 

We're looking forward to hosting you here. 

ABOUT US: 
We met in New York while attending a graduate program and bonded over our mutual passion for meditation. The lush nature and peacefulness of Seattle attracted us, so once the opportunity to move presented itself, we seized it right away.  After a drive across the country we felt at home here right away. This city is so magical and full of fond memories. 

We hope you'll have a fantastic and memorable stay with us.

name: Charming Fremont Craftsman with Scenic Views
description:
Step into classic Seattle charm at this remodeled 1909 Craftsman in the heart of Fremont. Enjoy dark fir floors, a bright kitchen, and a lovely back deck and yard. With a spacious dining room, cozy family room, and a guest suite, it's perfect for families and small groups. Walk to local shops and restaurants and take in the beautiful neighborhood and mountain views.

Add our listing to your wishlist by clicking the heart in the upper-right corner!
neighborhood_overview:
Welcome to Fremont, Seattle’s eclectic and vibrant neighborhood known for its unique blend of creativity, culture, and community spirit. Wander through streets adorned with public art, including the famous Fremont Troll and the whimsical Lenin statue.

Don’t miss the Sunday Fremont Market for local crafts and delicious food. Enjoy a leisurely stroll along the Burke-Gilman Trail or rent a kayak for a fun day on the water.

For foodies, Fremont offers a diverse culinary scene with must-visit spots like the Fremont Brewing Company, the iconic Paseo for mouth-watering sandwiches, and Revel for innovative Korean fusion.

Fremont truly has something for everyone – come and see why it’s known as the “Center of the Universe”!
host_about:
*Luxury Hotels Meet Vacation Rentals*

It's great to meet you! We're Recreation Vacation Rentals, a vacation rental management company based in Seattle, but we manage vacation homes throughout the US.

We were founded by two former hotel executives with the goal of bringing the same practices and processes from some of the best hotels in the world to the vacation rental industry to improve consistency and guest experience.

Where you stay should compliment your life and make it easy to live every facet, that's why we’ve focused our in-stay experience around the pillars of sleeping, working and living. Our goal is to create a space that meets your needs as they change throughout the day. We take what you love about hotels and what you appreciate about vacation rentals and bring them together into one perfect stay. 

We love the hospitality industry and can't wait to welcome you to one of our homes. Our team is here for you throughout your stay, ready to help with anything.

neighborhood_overview:
Much like New York City, Seattle is a city of neighborhoods, each with its own distinct personality. We live in Ballard, which has been called "the most soulful" neighborhood in Seattle. We think of it as the 21st arrondissement of Paris: the Farmers Market, the boutiques, the little coffee bars and boîtes. Our house is located one mile north of historic Ballard, close enough for a leisurely walk through this quaint, friendly neighborhood, and yet, far enough away to park easily and sleep undisturbed from others coming and going from all of the wonderful restaurants and bars this neighborhood has to offer!

More info about Ballard:
+ a 5-minute drive from Golden Gardens beach (with amazing sunset views of Elliot Bay and the Olympic Mountains)
+ a 20-minute drive from downtown (or, a 30-minute bus ride if you'd prefer to avoid the expense of parking)
+ a charming neighborhood, home to dozens of quaint boutiques, coffee shops, restaurants featuring many differen
host_about:
Hello!

In addition to being hosts, we are frequent Airbnb guests. We first stayed at an Airbnb location in Sydney, Australia, while honeymooning in January 2012, and were so impressed with our experience that we are now hooked! Not only are the Airbnb properties a good value, but more importantly, we have had amazing interactions with each of the hosts at locations where we've stayed, which now have expanded beyond Sydney, Australia, to include a handful of locations in our home state of Washington as well as cities throughout the U.S., and also other countries including Spain, Tanzania, France, Canada, England, Czech Republic, The Netherlands, and Germany. We've been a guest in more than 60 different Airbnb locations over the past 10 years. In fact, I can't remember the last time we stayed at a conventional hotel!

Since we had such great experiences as guests, we decided to start hosting in the summer of 2012 and listed our guest room on Airbnb. Hosting has proven to be a fantastic experience since we are both seasoned travelers and enjoy chatting with others about their travels, etc.

We are avid travelers and are also very tidy and respectful. Beyond travelling, we like listening to live music, exploring neighborhoods, having fun with our dogs, gardening, cooking great food, spending time near the water/beach, and meeting new people.

description:
Looking for a memory instead of another hotel in yet another city?
Welcome to Your Home in the Emerald City
We have a great and charming apartment in a 100 year old building in Seattle. just 1 block away from the University of Washington. Heart of university district, very near downtown and local stadiums. Huskies are a walk away. Seahawks and Mariners are just a bus ride away. We are just a block away from the post office. Outside your door Cuisine great spots for beer, dinner and activities.

host_about:
Hi there! My name is Shel and I am in the beautiful Pacific Northwest I heard about Airbnb through many of my friends and all of there experiences have been positive, so I figured I would jump on the band wagon.

I will be travelling to different parts of the world (Italy, Ireland, New York City and Hawaii) with my job over the next year and our beautiful apartment, one block from UW in Seattle, will be empty. We felt like it was such a shame to see it empty and none of our friends and family were available to use our space, so we figured we would try Airbnb!

I absolutely love what Seattle has to offer. I love the hikes, consistent fresh air and unbelievable scenery.

I play softball, and do so competitively nationwide, I am very active and love exploring new places in the city and surroundings.

Personally, 5 things I can't live without... sunshine, friends, community, great food and sports. I actually hold activities for the #2 food group (Seattle True Foodies) in the nation. I am also the secretary of the Seahawks Tailgate Crew. Rent my place and you will be my guest at our party.  Help up save for a place of our own.  I absolutely love life!

Well, that's me!

neighborhood_overview:
Beacon Hill is centrally located, right off I-5, by the West Seattle Bridge, the entrance to Highway 99 and the I-90 bridge to the Eastside. Beacon Hill is a diverse, LGBTQ-friendly and family neighborhood with views of downtown Seattle. Enjoy coffee, pastries, wine, locally brewed beer, Italian, Greek, Mexican, American, Fillipino food, all located within walking distance and available for take-out. Jefferson Park, a 10 minute walk has fabulous views of the city and sunset.

Take the light rail from the Beacon Hill Station, 3 short stops to the International District for Asian food, or take it 2 stops to Columbia City where you can enjoy food, movies, and music venues or 2 stops to Century Link/Lumen and T-Mobile stadiums to watch football, baseball, soccer or a musical event. Travel a more stops and you can get to Capitol Hill and the University of Washington.

name: Top of the Hill Garden Condo
description:
Peaceful, centrally located and a haven for pets.

Nestled in the friendly community of Capitol Hill sits this beautiful, well-furnished, fully stocked garden 1 bedroom /1 bathroom condo. Perfectly located, it's within walking distance to 15th and 19th Avenues East, each street hosting a vibrant restaurant, cafe, and shopping scene. Grocery stores, markets, hair salons, gyms, yoga and Pilates studios, schools, hospitals, florists, cafes, and 5-star restaurants all within walking distance.
host_about:
Born and raised in the Montana, my craze for mountain adventure was ignited by the awe-inspiring Rocky Mountains and led me to Seattle 30 years ago where I have climbed, scaled, scrambled, skied, criss-crossed, trudged, trekked, hiked, biked and kayaked some of the Pacific Northwest’s classic adventures and hidden gems.  

My impetus to see the world began with an obsession to climb in some of the world’s highest mountains. Trudging off to these remote areas to reach enticing peaks, I first discovered the joys of living with the mountain people. This has lead to speaking fluent Spanish, and spending a lot of her time in South America where she I had an adobe apartment in the bohemian district of Lima.

I have had a variety of careers all involving education and the environment:  I was the owner of an outdoor adventure company in Seattle, a program developer and educator, a coordinator for college environmental education, a back country crew leader for restoration and trail work in the North cascades and Alaska, a geologist in the Olympic National Park, wilderness guide in the Pacific Northwest and currently the co-founder and board member of Crooked Trails, a nonprofit international travel company as well as a Property manager and investor in real estate and short term rentals.

I would LOVE to help you create a spectacular, exciting, relaxing stay in Seattle!  I can offer suggestions, itineraries, tours and transport.

name: Charming Wallingford House
description: We call this gem "The Loft" because it feels like a downtown loft apartment. It's a century old craftsman house and you'll have it all to yourself. It is conveniently located in the Wallingford neighborhood near I5, bus routes, light rail, UW, and walking distance to several family owned restaurants, bars, shops and a grocery store. We love the globally diverse dining options and the quiet charm that Wallingford offers. We aimed for simplicity, no fees, and comfort. We hope you love it.
neighborhood_overview:
Wallingford is a well known and loved Seattle neighborhood. It's central to all mixed residential/commercial neighborhoods in the north end and offers everything you'll need. The University of Washington is 3 miles east, the Ballard locks and Golden Gardens are 4-5 miles west, Green Lake is 1.5 miles north and Fremont is 3 miles south. It's easy to get in and out of Wallingford, but you'll also enjoy what the neighborhood has to offer. The thriving arts and craft scene with locally owned shops is still in recovery following the COVID-19 lockdowns. The dining options range from Americana, Russian, Afghan, Vietnamese to Irish. Most east Asian cuisine is covered including fusion options. The best poke in Seattle is across the street, and two famous Seattle stapes, Ezell's Chicken and Dick's Drive-in are one block away.

Check out the wallyhood blog for the latest happenings.

neighborhood_overview:
Magnolia is a Seattle neighborhood located on a peninsula that is adjacent to Queen Anne and is surrounded by the Puget Sound. The neighborhood offers a relaxed and laid-back lifestyle despite being located within 3 miles (or 10 minutes) from Downtown Seattle. Magnolia is also a diverse neighborhood, filled with people of various backgrounds

Magnolia is accessible via three bridges that cross Interbay. Notably, Magnolia is surrounded on three sides by water. neighborhood_overview:
Northlake is a neighborhood in Seattle, Washington, that consists of the southern part of Wallingford, below N 40th Street. It is so named for being on the northern shore of Lake Union. Landmarks include the Northlake Shipyard, Gas Works Park, the Wallingford Steps art installation, and Ivar's Salmon House. Circa 1900, the eastern part of Northlake was known as Latona, and the John Stanford International School building was formerly the Latona School.[1] Nowadays, the name Latona is likely to refer to anywhere along Latona Ave. NE from Northlake north to NE 65th St. near Green Lake.

Northlake's main thoroughfares are N 34th Street (east- and westbound), N Northlake Way and N Pacific Street (northeast- and southwest-bound), and Wallingford Avenue N and Stone Way N (north- and southbound).

neighborhood_overview:
Beacon Hill is a mellow bedroom neighborhood with a diverse ethnic history. The old Beacon Hill School building atop the hill has been renovated into a thriving community center with a food courtyard. It is just next to the light rail transit station, which requires you to descend 160 feet underground on an elevator to "catch the light rail". The area offers several restaurants, local pubs, along with the Red Apple grocery store, a bank, gas station, etc. There is also a library...and some new--mixed with old...plus plenty of nice pastry/coffee options.

The nearby Jimi Hendrix Park has the African American Museum, as well as soccer playing fields, basketball courts, and a great running route towards Lake Washington which allows for some hill work. The park currently has some construction as it will be the new entrance to the upcoming I-90 "East Link" Light rail station towards Bellevue.

If driving, this location also has easy access to I-90 Freeway towards th
host_about:
Travel, good ethnic food, waterfalls, hot springs, a nice book, and a glass of red wine.  I have traveled a lot internationally, and locally--so please let me know if you have an interest for Seattle, and I can point you in the right direction.

As to the place, I prefer clean and somewhat minimalist--yet still homey and functional.  The kitchen has a big movable island that begs for chopping vegetables, and I like creating conversational arrangements with furniture to encourage people to share their stories.

As a host, I tend to be hands off as oftentimes at work or running around, so texting via Airbnb is the best way to contact me if you need something.

Your stay here helps us preserve our history. This adorable vacation private room is the perfect quant getaway only minutes from all the excitement of every Seattle has to offer.  Make yourselve at home, enjoy a community kitchen, fast wifi and closeness to many downtown attractions, craf
neighborhood_overview:
Walking distance to Green Lake Community Center, which is situated on the east side the Seattle's enormously popular Green Lake Park. The park is surrounded by a vibrant residential and business district, with a library, restaurants, coffee shops and shopping. The biggest attraction is the lake itself, drawing thousands of people a day to jog, walk or wheel around the 2.8-mile path that encircles the body of water. Popular activities include renting kayaks and other kinds of ater craft, and playiing in one of the many sports leagues that use the park.

Right on Greenlake, you will love this neighborhood: pedestrian friendly, family recreation, the zoo, library, trendy restaurants, cafes, tennis courts, fowing facilities, several bus routes. Easy access to I-5, HW 99. 1.5 miles to Downtown Seattle, 3 miles to Amazon headquarters, 4 miles to Starbucks headquarters/11 miles to Microsoft.
host_about:
Welcome to our community!  We have a team managing your stay.  We love our guests. I am a real estate professional, have a genuine interest in historical architecture, and a passion to show you the beauty and history of our area. My husband is a 5th generation Seattleite and I am native BC.  We love the outdoors
 
This is not just one of the areas I represent for my professional job. This is my home.  This is my community.

neighborhood_overview: This furnished apartment is situated in South Lake Union, a hub for Amazon and the Seattle Times as well as the entire biotech industry. It’s constantly buzzing thanks to the numerous bars, restaurants and food trucks. In Lake Union Park, along the water sits the Museum of History & Industry which highlights the city’s history as well as business and innovation. Locals often head out to the lake for boating and paddle boarding. This neighborhood is also the home of Denny Park, which is the oldest green space in the city. To access other parts of the city from here, simply hop on the streetcar.

We’re Blueground, a global proptech company with several thousand move-in-ready apartments in a growing number of major cities around the world. Each apartment is thoughtfully designed with exclusive furnishings, fully equipped kitchens, and incredible amenities – making every day a five-star experience. From day one, you’ll enjoy high-speed Wi-Fi, premium linens, and smart home entertainment. Plus, access to pools, gyms, and outdoor spaces in select buildings.

Why stress over your apartment? We provide a hassle-free alternative — a consistent, quality guest experience that starts even before you arrive. Because we let you book our most up-to-date apartment listings online, confirm with a click, pay securely, and check in easily. 

Even better? You can enhance your stay with car rentals, grocery delivery, laundry services, and more through our special partnerships. 

During your stay
Upon arrival, you’ll either be greeted personally by a Blueground team member or given self-check-in instructions. The entire apartment is yours! You’ll enjoy reliable support via email, phone, and our Guest App, where you can request everything from a home cleaning to extra towels. 

We’ll share all details upon confirmation of your stay.

name: Columbia City Secluded Apartment
description: Our garden apartment in Columbia City faces  a secluded back garden. Above the apartment is a long time Columbia City private home. The apartment large and comfortable is located on a dead end street leading to Genesee Park, Lake Washington Blvd and Seward Park. The home is walking distance to Columbia City commercial district with restaurants, groceries, theatres, jazz, and the Light Rail Station with access to greater Seattle.
neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is next to Genesee Park, a 57 acre park bordered by Lake Washington and the Mount Baker Rowing and Sailing Center and home to the annual Seafair Hydroplane races. It has soccer fields, baseball, tennis and basketball. Once on Lake Washington Blvd you can walk, jog or bike on a bike trail along the lake to Seward Park, a 300 acre peninsula jutting out into Lake Washington with biking, jogging, strolling and swimming and hiking through old growth forests seeing bald eagles and blue heron.

You can also walk along the park to Columbia City, a landmark historic district from 1893 with a revitalization of new Italian, Thai, local, Caribbean Seafood and Mexican restaurants, Columbia City Bakery and Bob's Meats, organic foods at PCC and the Wednesday Farmer's Market, Cinema at the Ark Lodge and Live Theatre at the Columbia City Theatre, Jazz at the Royal Room, Poke, juices, ice cream, coffee and great second use clothing and furniture stores, banks, post office, yoga

neighborhood_overview:
Once home to Jimi Hendrix and Quincy Jones, the Central District is an up-and-coming area that is – no surprise – centrally located in Seattle. It is vibrant and one of the most culturally diverse areas in the city. Next door from the lively Capitol Hill neighborhood, there are a good number of restaurants, hip bars and cafes, and you are close to other neighborhoods with a lot of excitement. It has easy access to major highways which makes getting in and around city fairly simple.

Central District is bordered on the north by Capitol Hill and Madison Valley, on the east by Madrona and Leschi, on the south by Atlantic, and on the west by the International District and First Hill.

description: The UW House is a centrally located Airbnb house perfect for budget travelers. Each private room is equipped with a key, fast internet, towels, desk and chair, fan in summer, space heater in winter, clothes rack, and mirror. neighborhood_overview:
Proudly named for the neighboring nationally renowned University of Washington, this house is located only a quarter mile from campus. Check out the Suzzallo library at the university for the closest thing to Harry Potter’s Hogwarts or if you are lucky enough to visit in the Spring take a post-worthy photo among the cherry blossoms of the main campus square.

This student neighborhood is always bustling with activity. You'll find an abundance of budget-friendly international restaurants, coffee shops, bookshops, and music venues just blocks away.

Please remember this neighborhood where the University and student housing are located so there may be the occasional weekend party, especially in the spring season. neighborhood_overview:
The home is nestled in the Judkins Park neighborhood. It is a centrally located neighborhood in Seattle that has long been home to people of diverse backgrounds. This area has grown and developed over time but still maintains its charm and character. It features beautiful architecture and some great parks. There are many things to do in this part of town like taking in the view from Volunteer Park.



Judkins Park is also home to many unique shops, cafes, and restaurants. The small business community in this part of town adds character, and it's one of the things that makes staying here so unique! There are also some great parks and walking trails just minutes from the front door. It's no wonder people love staying here – while there may be other areas nearby with more amenities right now, none offer such an authentic feel or friendly vibe as this one does.

I love to travel with my husband Ciaran, we hate being home bodies. More than likely you will find us; camping, hiking, & skiing through the PNW, exploring international destinations, sipping our way through the many wine regions of Washington State, or road tripping through our National Parks #vanlife. We have a 12 year old 15 pound long-haired dapple Dachshund named Charlie Brown. Charlie's favorite things are; cheese, carrots, belly rubs, barking unnecessarily, and lounging in the sun.   I am currently renting out the property to give me a little more financial freedom for our adventures and also to give anyone traveling to Seattle an affordable and comfortable way to explore the city.

neighborhood_overview:
Capital Hill is remembered as the birthplace of Grunge, and has always been open to alternative lifestyles. Capital Hill now may be Seattle's Foodie Epicenter!

Activity Suggestions??

Fun day with no car? Lightrail downtown and take water Taxi over to Alki Beach. Alki, on W Seattle, has fantastic views of Seattle & the sound + fun eateries and sandy beaches to walk.

Evenings, I highly suggest App Hopping, walk to a restaurant, sit at the bar, order a round & an Appetizer, ask the server/bartender for a "Where next suggestion" and keep going until the evening has filled you up. Pace yourself by visiting local independent businesses. It's how I visit every new destination and many known destinations :-)
host_about:
A Boston transplant since 2001, Seattle is a place I've come to love and call home (aside from super bowl conflicts!).  The geographic access to ocean, mountains, islands and rain forests is unsurpassed in my travels to date.  From an urban perspective, Seattle's commitment to local artistry provides  a world of exploration.

My Capitol Hill home was my first home purchase and inadvertently launched my current real estate career.  Now my passions are continuing the NW exploration and helping people realize their housing dreams.

host_about:

各位租客大家好！我来自中国，现在在美国生活了16年。我很幸运地结交了一群信任我的好朋友，她们说我善良，忠诚，可靠，热情，开朗，有趣。我有进取的心，有似水的梦怀，有崇高的理想。  我，幽默宽容。不喜欢看别人满面怒容的样子，我认为微笑才是天下最美的风景。“比大地宽阔的是海洋，比海洋宽阔的是天空，比天空宽阔的是人的心灵。”  我，积极进取。小小的我是一粒沙，但不甘于落后，一生庸碌无为。我，爱好跑步，热爱旅行，非常喜欢户外运动，渴望把生活中的美好事物分享给身边的朋友。比起旅行，我更加喜欢去学习当地的文化，了解他们的生活。我作为房东，在我的住宿里，我一定尽我所能为您提供一切便利，使您的旅行更加轻松愉快。感谢您驻留在我这里……

neighborhood_overview: With Amazon worldwide headquarters nearby, this neighborhood is vibrant and hi tech.  We are close to Unviersity of Washington, biotech hub of Lake Union. Many small parks dot the shore, including Fairview Park and Eastlake Bouledrome, which claims to have the best waterfront bocce ball in Seattle (though we can’t imagine there’s much competition for that title). It’s always fun to grab a table on the deck at one of the restaurants along the lake (like Eastlake Bar and Grill or Serafina) so you can watch the boats and seaplanes. name: 3BR Modern, High Ceilings & Close to Everything
description: This PNW-modern (aka modern but homey) townhouse makes an ideal home base for work & play. neighborhood_overview:
Magnolia is a quaint neighborhood right below the popular Ballard and Fremont neighborhoods and all the venues, restaurants, cafes, and shops they offer, while having a neighborhood feel. Or pop down to the city in no time flat (~10 mins) by car, by multiple nearby bus lines, or by bike (the Shipyard trail takes you right there, along the beautiful Puget Sound).

Magnolia is also the landmass on which the famous Discovery Park sits—a gorgeous 534-acre urban woodlands that cannot(!) be beat. It's fantastic for hiking, trail running, strolling, clearing you mind, watching sunsets, seeing orcas, having picnics, and (tough) biking; and it's a a 5-min car ride away or an 8-min mildly challenging bike ride just up Gilman Ave.

name: Relaxed sophistication in Mt. Baker
description:
You will love the beautifully remodeled, professionally designed studio apartment located on the ground floor of my Mt. Baker mid-century home. Comparable to a luxury hotel suite, the light filled apt. features a fireplace, and a bright stylish bath with heated floor, handmade tiles and mosaic work. Ideally located close to Lake Washington, Columbia City shops, restaurants, entertainment, Light Rail and buses. (No shoes or smoking inside.)

3 day minimum stay with certain exceptions.
neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is a favorite among Seattlites. Many Seattle city officials, judges, etc., choose to make their home here. There are many beautiful homes and gardens, making for lovely walks. Several gorgeous parks and the waterfront within easy walking distance will supply your nature fix. For your urban experience, there are shops, restaurants and entertainment, and public transportation within minutes. "The 98118," as the residents call it, is the most diverse zip code within the US- a fact we are very proud of! An unusual mix of socioeconomic levels and every ethnic group you can think of- hence the unbelievable array of ethnic restaurants and shops.
host_about:
I am a fun-loving world traveler, cook, gardener, artist and reader. One of my biggest pleasures in life is learning about a new place, new people, new food- both through my own travels and as a host.  My friends would describe me as active, open, engaging, funny and liberal. I was raised in the deep South of the USA (Georgia), the youngest of 5 siblings, but have lived in Seattle for 25+ years. Seattle is a hot bed of music talent, and I take advantage of it by staying updated on emerging talent and attending as many live performances as I can. I am often the oldest person there, but so what! You could not ask for a better city to live in if you are a foodie, as I am.  The variety here is unbelievable. My profession is Interior Design, so of course, design and art are an important part of my life. Books, and more books- don't even try to talk to me if I have a book in my hand!

I have three absolutely gorgeous and brilliant daughters who no longer live with me, which naturally makes them even more attractive! They live in Los Angeles and San Francisco and I visit them often.

My travels have included, but are not restricted to: most of the states within the USA, Canada, Mexico, Guatemala, Argentina, Cuba, France, Spain, Portugal, Italy, Croatia, Slovenia, Morocco, South Africa, Viet Nam, Cambodia, Laos, Thailand, and China. I love hiking, camping, and staying places off the beaten tourist path. I will always choose a host over a hotel- how better to really learn something about the place you bothered to travel?

Once upon a time, I spoke pretty decent Italian, but am rusty and out of practice. I would love some Italian guests to practice with (or rather, "with whom to practice", as I will claim to be a grammar expert). My French is even rustier. I have begun to study Spanish recently. I have a great love of the English language and grammar- yes, I was that person in school who loved diagramming sentences, and always had my hand in the air to answer the grammar questions while everyone else's eyes were rolling back in their heads! I am TESOL certified (Teacher of English as a Second Language), and hope to live abroad and teach at some point in my future. In the meantime, I have volunteered to teach English to refugees here in Seattle. Combining hosting and teaching have great appeal to me.

I can't live without: Spicy food, friends and family, some crafty project, music, art, fertile soil, books, travel, and my boyfriend.

host_about:
Jimi and I are super excited to be a part of the airbnb community. We have been hosting people for about three years now, and we have loved every minute of it. I (William) have lived in the Pacific Northwest for 20+ years. I know most of the great spots to experience a good bite or an amazing sunset. Jimi is originally from the Philippines and brings his amazing flair to our home. 

We started hosting people on airbnb because my father is half paralyzed.  We use the money from airbnb to help support him as he cannot support himself. So we treat every guest as the blessing they are, a helping hand to my father's better fortunes. We have recently added a few extra units to see if we can start a little boutique hotel. Thank you so much for considering our home and we look forward to meeting you on the next adventure.

name: Ballard oasis in the pacific Northwest
description:
Our Ballard home is a little oasis tucked into a quiet urban residential neighborhood. We have a large back yard with a lavender, cherry blossom, apple, pear, and plum trees.
This is a great home for a family or couple wanting to explore Seattle. Entire home is yours! 6-7 night minimum stay. However, if we have a few open days in the calendar we sometimes are happy to accommodate a shorter stay.
neighborhood_overview: Ballard has a rich history and is respected as one of the hippest areas in all of Seattle. One of Ballard’s most-visited attractions is the Hiram M. Chittenden Locks, which were built in 1917. Engineering buffs will enjoy the well-orchestrated mechanics of it all, and dreamers can imagine sunning themselves on the huge yachts that pass through. You can also go to the underwater observatory and watch the salmon swimming up the fish ladder on their way to Lake Washington and beyond. In the summer months, Golden Gardens Park is a major destination. It’s one of the few sandy beaches in Seattle, and you’ll find beach volleyball courts, kite flyers, sand castles, and barbecue pits. Sure, the water is still frigid, but on the right day you feel just like you’re in Maui. Every Sunday during the year, the Ballard Farmer’s Market is open for business. Ballard Avenue is closed down to make room for local growers and vendors, plus a variety of artists selling their wares, from jewelry to furniture
host_about: I have been an art teacher for 22 years and we like to travel and see new places during the summer.  We also like to create an affordable and relaxing place for people like ourselves who want to travel on a budget.   We love our home and hope you will too.

Looking for the ultimate location with ease of access to Seattle & the Greater Puget Sound region? Look no further!

Whether you are on a work trip, catching an event downtown, taking a cruise, or just need centralized access to the city, this is your spot!

Upon arrival, you’ll either be greeted personally by a Blueground team member or given self-check-in instructions. The entire apartment is yours! You’ll enjoy reliable support via email, phone, and our Guest App, where you can request everything from a home cleaning to extra towels.

Just 10 minutes north of Ballard, a hip, historic neighborhood in Seattle's northwest corner known as a hotspot for new restaurants and bars, urban development, and Scandinavian heritage. Fremont is 10 minutes. Downtown Seattle is just a 20-minute ride or drive away, where the Seattle Aquarium, Waterfront, Pike Place Market, Seattle Art Museum and more await. The University of Washington is also easily accessible by car or Metro (15-20 minutes).

For those who want to explore the woods or beach, our cottage is just a half-mile walk to the Piper's Creek Trailhead South Eddie McAbee Entrance, part of the large, forested Carkeek Park and Piper's Creek watershed. name: The Carriage House
description: Cozy comfort with great character. Cedar posts, old growth Douglas fir beams, rich concrete stained floors and counter tops. In residential neighborhood walking distance to beautiful Greenlake. 10% of your payment is donated to the home owners' nonprofit First Aid Arts to help trauma survivors find hope and healing.
neighborhood_overview: Located just north of beautiful Greenlake between I-5 and Aurora in a residential neighborhood, The Carriage House's central location makes it easy to get to most parts of Seattle within 15-20min. We love to sail and paddle board on Greenlake (you can rent everything there), get great coffee and artisan chocolates at Chocolati Cafe, grocery shop at PCC organic market and enjoy eating at the many great restaurants in the area. host_about:
I'm a professional musician and the founder of a Seattle-based non profit organization called First Aid Arts. Our team trains organizations all over the world in how to use creative expression as a tool for recovery from traumatic experiences like human trafficking, war and natural disaster. (Learn more about our work with an internet search of First Aid Arts!)
Having lived in Hawaii, the San Juan Islands, Bellingham and Seattle, I love sailing, surfing, skateboarding, traveling with purpose, and spending time with my wife and two kids. While studying abroad I had the opportunity to be hosted by local families in various parts of Central America and Europe. Our family enjoys being able to extend the same kind of hospitality through Airbnb. We look forward to meeting you!

host_about:
Hi there! My name is Shel and I am in the beautiful Pacific Northwest I heard about Airbnb through many of my friends and all of there experiences have been positive, so I figured I would jump on the band wagon.

I will be travelling to different parts of the world (Italy, Ireland, New York City and Hawaii) with my job over the next year and our beautiful apartment, one block from UW in Seattle, will be empty. We felt like it was such a shame to see it empty and none of our friends and family were available to use our space, so we figured we would try Airbnb!

I absolutely love what Seattle has to offer. I love the hikes, consistent fresh air and unbelievable scenery.

I play softball, and do so competitively nationwide, I am very active and love exploring new places in the city and surroundings.

Personally, 5 things I can't live without... sunshine, friends, community, great food and sports. I actually hold activities for the #2 food group (Seattle True Foodies) in the nation. I am also the secretary of the Seahawks Tailgate Crew. Rent my place and you will be my guest at our party.  Help up save for a place of our own.  I absolutely love life!

Well, that's me!

Surrounded by dining, shopping, arts and culture, there's never a dull moment or shortage of adventure here. This community is smoke free, pet friendly and our residents create a welcoming sense of community, making it one of the most amazing places to call home during your stay.  The Central Waterfront was once the hub of Seattle's maritime activity. Since the construction of a container port to its south in the 1960s, the area has increasingly been converted to recreational and retail uses. This charming townhouse Master bedroom is perfect for family & friends looking to experience Seattle’s unique mix of urban excitement and laid-back, Northwest charm. Located just steps from some of the best breweries, coffee shops, restaurants, Sunday's farmer market and boutique shops in Ballard, this home offers both comfort and convenience.
neighborhood_overview: Discover the essence of Ballard as you explore its picturesque streets. Our neighborhood boasts a delightful blend of historic charm and modern convenience. Stroll down to the Ballard Locks and watch boats navigate the Ship Canal, or visit the stunning Golden Gardens Park for a dose of natural beauty. Ballard is renowned for its thriving culinary scene, and you'll find a treasure trove of restaurants, coffee shops, and breweries just steps away. Savor artisanal dishes, sip on locally roasted coffee, and sample craft brews at numerous establishments within easy reach. When you stay with us, you'll be right in the heart of the action. Explore boutique shops, and art galleries, and experience the local culture that makes Ballard unique. And don't forget the Ballard Farmers Market, a Sunday tradition that offers fresh produce and artisanal goods. Our cozy Airbnb is your comfortable haven in this dynamic neighborhood. Whether you're here for work or leisure, you'll find our location conveni

name: Lake cottage @ Pritchard Beach - near down town
description: Relax by the fire & take in views in our stand-alone Cottage at Pritchard Beach, on tranquil Pritchard Island.  Our island is a little-known paradise in Seattle's city limits. It's quiet here. You are surrounded by beautiful Lake Washington to E, 2 min. walk to beach/park to the N, Pritchard Wetlands & Trails to the W, and Urban Farm to the S, Airport - 12 min., downtown - 15 min., Pike Place Market, Seahawks, Mariners, Sounders, Huskies. Columbia City - 5 min., Light Rail, Seward Park, seafair.
neighborhood_overview: Pritchard Island is a small community.  We have 1 street that runs the length of the island - about 3 blocks long with cul de sac.  We  are completely surrounded by water and parks. Seattle's bus system is extensive, reliable and efficient.  Seattle's new Light Rail is nearby.  An all-day pass is $5.00 and will get you downtown, Safeco Field, and UW.  Columbia City is a 5 minute drive and has a good sampling of restaurants, bars, a theater, PCC natural market, art galleries, bakery, etc.  Take your morning run around Seward Park's waterfront loop (2.5 miles) or go cross country through the park's trail system and experience the only remaining old-growth forest in Seattle.  The park has beautiful waterfront tennis courts and a swimming beach too.
host_about: Born and raised in the San Juan Islands - WA state - USA.  I now live in Seattle. I love to travel off the beaten path and mingle with the 'natives' - avoid resorts whenever possible.

neighborhood_overview: This furnished apartment is situated in South Lake Union, a hub for Amazon and the Seattle Times as well as the entire biotech industry. It’s constantly buzzing thanks to the numerous bars, restaurants and food trucks. In Lake Union Park, along the water sits the Museum of History & Industry which highlights the city’s history as well as business and innovation. Locals often head out to the lake for boating and paddle boarding. This neighborhood is also the home of Denny Park, which is the oldest green space in the city. To access other parts of the city from here, simply hop on the streetcar.

There are several stores, bars, restaurants, cafes, outdoor activities, and much more all within a few blocks of us.

neighborhood_overview: Walking distance to Green Lake Community Center, which is situated on the east side the Seattle's enormously popular Green Lake Park.  The park is surrounded by a vibrant residential and business district, with a library, restaurants, coffee shops and shopping.  The biggest attraction is the lake itself, drawing thousands of people a day to jog, walk or wheel around the 2.8-mile path that encircles the body of water.  Popular activities include renting kayaks and other kinds of ater craft, and playiing in one of the many sports leagues that use the park.

We hope you have a wonderful time!

description:
The room features wood cabin-like panels, a queen sized bed, an East-facing window and corner desk. This is a clean house that is quiet and well taken care of. There is free parking outside and guests will have access to a shared bathroom, kitchen and laundry room.

Basic amenities such as toiletries and laundry detergent will be provided. Long-term guests: please be prepared to purchase your own products.

I live 4 miles north of UW and 7 miles north of downtown Seattle.
host_about:
Hello, my name is Neil and I look forward to hosting you. I am a Seattle native that recently graduated from the University of Washington. I've been hosting for over a year now and have been fortunate enough to meet people like you who have come to Seattle for business, family and vacation.

I am currently working as a researcher at Seattle Children's Hospital while finishing up a few courses before I apply to medical school. Although I am busy most of the day, I hope you enjoy your time here.  I can give you recommendations, tell you about my experiences with airbnb, or serve you a really nice cup of tea. 

I am looking for guests that are friendly and self-sufficient. I always try to make myself available but with my busy schedule I also ask for your patience and understanding. 

Let me know if you have any questions and I'll be happy to answer them.

name: Cozy charming 1 bedroom apartment
description: Private, cozy, and comfortable 1 bedroom, 3/4 bath downstairs apartment with a separate entrance. Located in Seattle's Columbia City/Seward Park neighborhood, a walk-able, safe area. We're about 5 miles from downtown Seattle. It's a pleasant, 15 minute walk to the lively, eclectic Columbia City business district, and about a 20 minute walk to the Columbia City light rail station. Beautiful Seward Park is a 15 minute stroll in the other direction. We have the best of all worlds here!
neighborhood_overview: We are in walking distance of Columbia City, home to an eclectic mix of boutiques, restaurants, and coffee shops, the Columbia City Bakery and PCC Natural Market. Hear excellent live music at the Royal Room or catch a film at the Ark Lodge Cinema. For nature lovers, we are  walking distance to Seward Park with its 120 acres of old growth forest, 3 miles of shoreline along Lake Washington, open spaces and pathways originally designed by the Olmsted Brothers.
host_about: We look forward to hosting you! I'm a mom, a musician and a curious consumer of life. I lead the Columbia City Community Chorus (now on Zoom til easier times return), compose, teach, and play in a band called The Go Janes. I love to hike, ski and travel, especially off the beaten path. I've been to some pretty remarkable places (Bolivia, Syria, India) but truthfully my favorite place to explore is the Pacific Northwest. I grew up here, and there's still so much more to see! As a host, I love meeting people and creating a sense of welcome. Airbnb is such a great, affordable way to connect with people and have a unique and authentic travel experience.

name: Stylish Flat in Iconic West Seattle
description: Welcome to this custom designed ground level apartment in the desirable Belvidere neighborhood of West Seattle. Every detail was thoughtfully created to maximize every inch of it's swanky 800sqft of spacious living. Recently completed in January 2019, this unit personifies the Pacific Northwest with a modern twist. You are greeted with polished pebble concrete floors, expansive ice white kitchen countertops, stainless steel appliances, charcoal stained maple cabinets and alder wood finishes.
neighborhood_overview: Access, access, access! This propert is located in a fantastic community with a myriad of activities and a variety of shops and restaurants. The location is perfect for hopping on the freeway, BUT not so close that you can hear or see it! It is also ideal for walking to everything... parks and Alki beach are nearby. We could list all of our favorite spots in West Seattle but it would take too much of your time to read! We love the beach, city and mountain views from various parks around our neighborhood and walking up to the Alaska Junction which takes 8-10 minutes where you will find a myriad of boutiques, shops, restaurants, cultural venues and nightlife.
host_about:
I have lived in Seattle all of my life and wouldn't live anywhere else. I tried! After living/working abroad and seeing other countries, I realized our "Emerald City" is where I belong. I went to culinary school and love to share that passion with our guests. I currently work independently and stay at home with our two young children. 

We can't live without things to do which is everything the Pacific NW has to offer AND within easy reach! We can go clam-digging just outside our neighborhood or in 45 minutes find ourselves  skiing at Snoqualmie Pass. 

My husband David (a California transplant) has been a Seattleite for over  22 years and obviously loves it here! He has  been with the Seattle Fire Department for 19 years and cherishes what he does. We both  coach youth sports for the YMCA and WSSC and cherish spending time with our family. 
We believe the Pacific NW's best kept secret is:  It really doesn't rain as much as they say! Everything that surrounds you... the city, mountains and water are just absolutely transcending! Our summers here are bar-none with the most spectacular long days of sunlight.

description: *Beautiful artsy home  *Partial Mt Rainier view *Private location w/parking! Spacious treetop room  (174sf) has a sweet sleeping alcove and an extra twin bed.  Kitchen is great.
