neighborhood_overview:
I love my neighborhood for all the reasons I've listed above, and because of the community feel here. The Fremont Arts Council and the Fremont Abbey for arts and performance oriented creativity and activities, the Chamber for growing and sustaining businesses, and the local color everywhere. Walking along the Burke Gilman Trail at the base of Phinney Avenue by the life sized dinosaur topiaries is a great way to spend time and get a ground level view of the canal and all the boats and ships that pass by. Stopping at the Lighthouse Roaster for incredibly delicious coffee and a variety of teas gives you a taste of a local and very popular neighborhood meeting place.
Following the many connecting stairways and paths in the area gives you a very special experience of this great neighborhood. There is a newly finished neighborhood stair case on Greenwood Avenue. Great for step training!

Link to typical tourist sites and some great alternatives:
(URL HIDDEN) hidd
host_about:
I love art and "creation." I love to travel.  I look forward to winter snowshoeing, some US travel, hosting on airbnb and a trip to Germany (Autumn 2019).  2020 will be my 8th year as an airbnb host.   I speak French and Spanish (much better French) and I have worked in education, real estate, video, and parade art ensemble builds. 

My home is in the "center of the Universe" in the artsy and eclectic Fremont area - where you find the Troll under Aurora bridge, a great PCC coop, banks, shops, cafes, and a great night life as well.  

2020 Holiday Season
Holiday events in and around Fremont include the lighting of the Lenin Statue (for real), a parade of caroling boats creating truly heavenly sounds, the annual Winter Feast on or close to Dec 21, great shopping for unique gifts at all the local shops, First Friday art walk, New Years Eve spectacular fire works on Lake Union, and access to all the Seattle 2020 holiday excitement including the Nutcracker with the Pacific Northwest Ballet, and Seattle Symphony's New Years Eve Party!  

Summer Solstice
The famous Fremont Solstice Parade happens every June close to summer solstice.  Creator of the Ice Queenistas 2009-2012  I was an Ice Queen Clown in 2014  and accompanied a 7 foot articulated wolf/dog made from reed and white papier machee created by local artist, Sarah Lovett. In 2015 I was a banner carrier with the lead Samba ensemble group Girasol.  

The Neighborhood
As to the Fremont neighborhood, I moved here years ago thinking I'd stay a couple of years but many lattes, parades  and  3 homes later, I'm still here.  We have a smaller community of artsy, smart and creative people with heart, in the middle of the big city.  I live on a hill and have a great view of Mt Rainier on a sunny / clear day from one of the rooms and the back deck.  And it's always great to come home to this charming and awesome neighborhood.

FOODIE w/o gluten!!
After years, and maybe more years, I'm pretty much gluten and heavy carb free.  My cooking includes salads, chicken, veggies both raw and cooked, broths and soups, coffee, tea, coconut and chocolate desserts.  Love coconut oil and fresh salmon.
But I taste just about everything and never turn my nose up my guests regional cooking shares.

MORE...
For myself living without the open road, great friends, dream time, and my favorite shoes including some well seasoned ostrich boots from the Boot Lady in Seattle, is not an option.  

AND along with 2 treetop rooms upstairs, the cute and lovable 1 bedroom apartment is available for you too.  With a full kitchen and bath, and a great 40" Vizio flat screen that works with your chrome cast service,  you will love it. If you want extra privacy, your own fridge and cooking space,  and/or room for a couple of friends to travel with you, pick this option.  If you want 100% remodeled please continue your search.  If you love the unique and artistic life, clean, well supplied and situated on a country lane in the city do check out "Super cool in artsy Fremont"!     

Favorite coffee - Lighthouse Roaster from right up the street at 43rd and Phinney.
Favorite view - from the sun dial at the top of Gas Works Park hill.
Favorite Seattle park - Discovery Park
What I think about Eastern WA - it's an excellent secret - with wide open valleys, rolling hills, rivers, wheat fields and when the rain is over the top in Seattle, there's nearly always SUN!

How I feel about Puget Sound - big love - have to hop a ferry at least a few times a year to visit an Island or the Olympic Penninsula; have to walk on a gravel beach and skip a few rocks to remember the incomparable beauty of the place; seagulls make me happy.  Mt. Rainier is my sacred mountain - it calls me each year at least once to hike or snowshoe and feel the awesome presence of its magnetic core.  

I love traveling in France and Europe in general, Mexico, the American West and Southwest, and now, South America.  My favorite way to travel is to friends or family who live there.  Or with a group of like minded people on a small group tour.  Or by car locally and in the Southwest where the wide open spaces bring freedom to my soul.

name: Queen Anne Oasis
description: Large groups will rest easy at this newly renovated 5-bedroom luxury home with private guest suite. This gem is centrally located in one of Seattle’s most charming and desirable neighborhoods. Walk along quaint, tree-lined streets to restaurants and shopping on Queen Anne Avenue or catch the bus a block away for a quick 10-minute ride to the popular Seattle Center and downtown. Afterwards, enjoy dinner or a glass of wine on the beautiful fenced-in outdoor patio or a soak in the warm swim spa.
neighborhood_overview:
OUR LOCATION

The Queen Anne neighborhood is a historic part of Seattle, with gracious mansions sitting side by side with vibrant shops and trendy restaurants – like Crow, which serves new American fare in hip digs and Canlis, a historic lake view fine dining establishment.

From my home you can walk to Seattle Pacific University and the Interlay Golf Course, both less than a mile away. If you’re a water lover, head over to Lake Union, 2 miles away, and rent a kayak or a paddle board for the day. If you're not into getting into the car, catch one of three buses lines that run along 10th Ave West outside the door - taking you downtown, Seattle Science Center and more.

Come in June, when Fremont hosts the Solstice Festival, or live it up at Oktoberfest in the fall. Whenever you come, Seattle will welcome you with open arms!
host_about:
After my husband passed away, my daughter and I renovated our Queen Anne home. We renovated with the intentions of creating a Four Seasons Airbnb, hosting guests from all over the world, while we travel all over the world.  We added an additional floor, putting all the bedrooms on one floor. We opened up the main floor and built an amazing kitchen and living room. The dining room table seats eight, with kids seating for 6 close by! We turned the downstairs into a private Guest Suite. Our house was inspired by all the fabulous hotels we've stayed and ships we've sailed. We're calling our home the Queen Anne Oasis. Everything from the heated floors, towel warmers, and swim spa is the best. We want your visit to Queen Anne to be five stars all the way. 

The Queen Anne Oasis is for everyone, especially kids. My daughter created a game closet will all our favorite games. We've also left our bikes, scooters, and unicycles for our guests to use. 

My daughter and I are currently traveling, Queen Anne Oasis makes that possible. Throughout the house, you will see art that we've collected around the world and personal photos that tell our story. 

We'd love to host you on your visit to the Emerald City.

neighborhood_overview:
Capitol Hill/First Hill is one of the most interesting and fun neighborhoods in Seattle. Long ago it was an artistic neighborhood with a quirky/funky vibe, the area retains much of such character.

Many of Seattle's top coffee shops, restaurants, and bars, are right in Capitol Hill. It's also the most walkable neighborhood in Seattle or even the whole Northwest. It's an easy walk to Downtown, Space Needle, Pike Place Market, and South Lake Union. The famous Starbucks Reserve Roastery & Tasting Room is only 1 block away that you have to check it out.

There are also grocery stores/supermarkets, delis, pharmacies, gyms, yoga studios within walking distance in the neighborhood.

name: Comfortable Room in Modern Townhome
description: Enjoy a comfortable room in this modern Magnolia townhome.  Private bathroom.  Street parking.  Share a full modern kitchen, and rooftop deck with nice territorial views.  Bus lines steps away are very convenient.  Close to Ballard, bike paths northeast and south, Discovery Park, Ballard Locks, Magnolia Village, neighborhood pubs, restaurants, grocery.
neighborhood_overview: You're as close or as far away as you want to be here.  The neighborhood pubs nearby are comfortable and fun, with good food and drink.  Discovery Park is one of the biggest in the city (and arguably the most scenic), and the Locks are fun to cruise around on your way into or out of Ballard.  Magnolia Village is just up the hill, and offers more shops and restaurants.  The cruise ship terminal is seconds away by cab.  If you bike or run, the views from Magnolia Boulevard are spectacular, as they are from other points around the bluff as well.  A bike path south will take you into downtown along the waterfront (and past the cruise ship terminal as well), totally great; hook up with it to the northeast to bike or jog into Fremont, or even South Lake Union.  You can walk to Ballard from here (~25 min)... plenty of different ways to enjoy your stay.  The train yard down the hill makes a little noise sometimes, but it's not usually an issue.
host_about:
I teach high school physical education and health.  I also coach high school sports (cross country; swimming; track).  Formerly worked in business management.  All in the Seattle area.

description: Step into a beautifully curated 1918 craftsman with 2 bedrooms, 2 baths, and custom decor in every corner. neighborhood_overview: Welcome to West Seattle! Nestled across the bay from downtown, West Seattle offers a vibrant, laid-back community vibe with a mix of natural beauty, local charm, and city convenience. Enjoy easy access to Alki Beach, where you can stroll the scenic waterfront, dine at local cafes, or catch stunning sunsets over the Puget Sound. West Seattle is known for its lush parks, including Lincoln Park, which features forested trails, beachfront picnic spots, and panoramic views. The Junction area serves as the neighborhood’s lively heart, filled with unique shops, farm-to-table restaurants, and a welcoming atmosphere. With a quick water taxi ride or drive, downtown Seattle is always within reach. Experience the perfect blend of relaxation and urban excitement in West Seattle!
host_about:
Hi, I'm Crystal!

In 2016 I took the road trip of a lifetime intending to move from St. Louis to San Fransico. While on a pitstop in Seattle, I stayed in an AirBNB where the host said he just left San Fransico because Seattle was better. After that conversation my road trip ended early. I took his word and ended up renting a 1 bed/1 bath in Seattle. I enjoyed my AirBNB experience so much I listed my personal apartment. Since 2016 I've rented out 3 more of my personal spaces and have helped others list their own spaces. I love styling homes and creating a fun and unique experience for guests. I hope all my guests come to fall in love with Seattle, just as I did.

name: Lovely loft in historic downtown Seattle
description:
Beautiful, open, and light-filled loft apartment in Pioneer Square, Seattle. This spacious loft features high ceilings, large windows, natural wood floors, and amenities for a comfortable stay.

Located in the heart of the city's historic district, right next to a waterfall park, you'll be steps away from all the stadiums, as well as many restaurants, boutiques, museums, and more.

The studio comes equipped with a lofted queen-sized bed; steps are required to reach the bed.
neighborhood_overview:
Pioneer Square is the charming, bustling historic district in downtown Seattle. The neighborhood features some of Seattle's prized architecture, cobblestone alleyways, and a great gallery and restaurant scene. It's centrally located and within walking distance to the stadiums and most popular destinations downtown.

Please note that there are a few homeless shelters and missions in the area, as is common in many urban neighborhoods. However, we have never had any issues with resident or guest safety--in fact, most praise our building's location--and Pioneer Square is considered to be a very safe part of Seattle. For those prospective guests who are averse to seeing homeless people or panhandlers, I suggest avoiding downtown Seattle altogether.
host_about: I was raised in Seattle and have called this city home for over thirty years. I'm familiar with many of the city's neighborhoods and eateries, so don't hesitate to ask for recommendations.  (She/her)

neighborhood_overview:
Capitol Hill is a vibrant and eclectic neighborhood located in the heart of Seattle, making it an ideal destination for guests seeking a dynamic urban experience. Known for its lively atmosphere, diverse culture, and rich history, Capitol Hill offers a plethora of attractions and activities to explore.

At the heart of Capitol Hill is Broadway, lined with trendy boutiques, eclectic shops, hip cafes, and gourmet restaurants serving cuisine from around the world. The neighborhood is a haven for foodies, with a wide array of dining options ranging from cozy brunch spots to upscale eateries and late-night diners.

Art and culture: There are numerous art galleries, theaters, and performance venues showcasing local talent and international acts. The historic Harvard-Belmont District is home to beautiful mansions and stately homes, providing a glimpse into the neighborhood's past.

neighborhood_overview: With Amazon headquarters nearby, this neighborhood is vibrant and hi tech.  We are close to Unviersity of Washington, biotech hub of Lake Union.  There are lots of ways to get out and enjoy Lake Union here. There is a boat launch for kayaks and canoes, or you can join the Lake Union Crew squad. Many small parks dot the shore, including Fairview Park and Eastlake Bouledrome, which claims to have the best waterfront bocce ball in Seattle (though we can’t imagine there’s much competition for that title). It’s always fun to grab a table on the deck at one of the restaurants along the lake (like Eastlake Bar and Grill or Serafina) so you can watch the boats and seaplanes. If you’ve got the time, you can go on your very own seaplane ride and get a great view of Seattle, and Eastlake of course!

name: Convenient Location in Seattle's U District
description:
Walk score 98! Bike score 96! This 2 bedroom apartment is close to everything Seattle, including the UW campus.
A free parking spot is included, but you may prefer walking to restaurants, cafes, coffee shops and nightlife.
Seattle's best retail destination and collection of eateries, University Village, is also nearby.
Two bedrooms, a workspace and a kitchenette provide a fantastic place to stay while experiencing the youthful relaxed urban lifestyle of Seattle's U District.
neighborhood_overview:
There’s plenty to pique your interest in this cultural and educational hub.

The University District is a relaxed area with casual hangouts and a youthful feel.

Discover eclectic shops, global eats, world-class arts and entertainment, all waiting to be explored in one of Seattle's most unique neighborhoods.

Informal eateries, coffeehouses and quirky shops line University Way, known as "The Ave".

Husky Stadium at the waterside UW campus draws big crowds for college football.

Nearby parks include University Playground, Christie Park and Cowen Park.

View contemporary works at the Henry Art Gallery (15th Ave NE & NE 41st St) and fossils, regional Indigenous art, and cultural artifacts at the stunning Burke Museum (4303 Memorial Way NE).

For an outdoor adventure, rent a canoe or kayak at UW’s Waterfront Activities Center (3710 Montlake Blvd NE).
Nearby Portage Bay is also popular for kayaking.

I am grateful to be a part of your journey.

host_about:

description:
Welcome to Seattle Urban Village on Lake Union! You will have a new, clean and modern place to stay after an all day adventure in Seattle. Fully stocked community kitchen, your private room, shared bath, new bed, new mattress, fresh linens and towels. Close to the beach, downtown and everything Seattle has to offer.

neighborhood_overview: There are lots of ways to get out and enjoy Lake Union here. There is a boat launch for kayaks and canoes, or you can join the Lake Union Crew squad. Many small parks dot the shore, including Fairview Park and Eastlake Bouledrome, which claims to have the best waterfront bocce ball in Seattle (though we can’t imagine there’s much competition for that title). It’s always fun to grab a table on the deck at one of the restaurants along the lake (like Eastlake Bar and Grill or Serafina) so you can watch the boats and seaplanes. If you’ve got the time, you can go on your very own seaplane ride and get a great view of Seattle, and Eastlake of course!

This intimate home can comfortably accommodate 4 people.

neighborhood_overview:
The Seattle Sapphire is located in the Montreux Condominium in Belltown, the heart of Downtown Seattle. Right outside of the building, the streets are bustling with locals and visitors dining at nearby eateries, shopping at boutiques, and strolling by to get to the farmers market at Pike Place Market or to visit the nearby attractions at the Space Needle. If you pick up a beautiful flower bouquet at Pike Market, place it in the sapphire blue vase provided in the condo till you are ready to take it home with you!

The neighborhood is safe and filled with a lot of life! There is a grocery store across the street, but if you don't feel like cooking in the condo, walk around and find something that will tickle your taste buds and entice you to go back for more! For a quick coffee pick me up, visit the Artisan Cafe around the corner or try a delicatessen at La Parisienne French Bakery. Other popular eateries near The Seattle Sapphire include Biscuit B*tc# and Serious Pie. Other

Short-term operator license STR-OPLI-19-000668
neighborhood_overview:
Our guests love the neighborhood: "It's hard to beat the location. Mount Baker is a beautiful old neighborhood; you can walk east down the hill through charming streets to Lake Washington." "We loved that it was a very quick walk to Lake Washington for spectacular lakefront views of the cascades- breathtaking when you have clear skies." "One of my favorite neighborhoods in Seattle!"

Mt Baker is a charming historic neighborhood close to all the downtown attractions, and particularly convenient for Pioneer Square, Capital Hill and the waterfront. Its leafy streets, lakeside location and relaxed vibe make for a comfortable and welcoming break.

Lots of parks, several nice public beaches along Lake Washington, and excellent bike routes make this a great neighborhood for both kids and adults. Our house faces a park-like boulevard where neighbors gather to walk their dogs and play frisbee.

Good dining and shopping options are close at hand. Walk to Mio Po

We have traveled extensively with our family, and recently took 8 months off to travel around the world (staying in Airbnb's or course).  Favorite recent destinations:  Sri Lanka, Jordan, Netherlands, Nepal.

neighborhood_overview:
Central Seattle is at the heart of it all, with Judkins Park being one of the most popular parks in the neighborhood for skating, playing with puppies, frisbee and basketball. We have a ton of food options a short stroll away, and the hottest restaurants in Capitol Hill just a hop of an Uber ride away (less than $10).

Top 10 things to do within a 10 min radius (Walk or Uber):

1. Watch a fish fly at Pike Place Fish (or catch one as a VIP), or check out the first Starbucks in the world.
2. Stroll to Seattle Fish Guys for lunch - they have fresh seasonal selections of poke, oysters, sea urchins and seafood stews
3. Uber to Seattle Center to check out the Space Needle, Chihuly Glass Museum and Museum of Pop Music
4. Enjoy a cuppa at Starbucks Reserve on First Hill, and watch coffee beans pour out from through massive copper pipes along the ceiling (Charlie and the chocolate factory style)
5. Bar and restaurant hop on Capitol Hill - try an infamou

name: NEW Beautiful Suite Next to Vibrant Green Lake
description:
Newly custom rebuilt 1100sf private guest suite next to vibrant Green Lake, with everything at your fingertips. Half block to the lake, restaurants, grocery stores and bus lines. Minutes to downtown, zoo, hospitals, Fremont, Ballard, Uni of Wash...

3br/1 bath, chef's kitchen, living area, dining table, breakfast counter. 3rd br includes pro office chair, desk & sofa bed. Perfect for couples, adventurers, business travelers, families with kids. Free parking onsite & street. 1Gbps Internet.
neighborhood_overview:
Green Lake is one of the best places to live in Washington. Green Lake park is also one of Seattle's most beloved parks. Its expanse of water and green space draws people from all over the world. The park serves as a natural preserve for hundreds of species of trees and plants, as well as numerous birds and waterfowl. The 2.8-mile path around the lake provides a perfect recreational spot for runners, bikers, skaters and walkers. Many others use the athletic fields or visit the park for boating, picnics and swimming.

Coffee shops, taverns and restaurants are plentiful in the neighborhood. Most of them are located along the shores of the lake, but the urban explorer will stumble on a few eateries scattered throughout the neighborhood. You can find cuisine of all kinds, but Green Lake is not a neighborhood of chain restaurants and big box stores. Individually owned small businesses are part of what make the neighborhood so quaint.
host_about: We are an active family of 3 and enjoy traveling extensively all over the world to experience different cultures, food, meeting people and adventuring. We love being outdoors in the beautiful Pacific Northwest.

During your stay

neighborhood_overview: Ballard is a historic neighbourhood located in Seattle. description: Feel at home wherever you choose to live with Blueground. You’ll love this sophisticated South Lake Union furnished one bedroom apartment with its modern decor, fully equipped kitchen, and comfortable living room with great views. Ideally located, you’re close to all the best that Seattle has to offer! (ID #SEA189)
neighborhood_overview: This furnished apartment is situated in South Lake Union, a hub for Amazon and the Seattle Times as well as the entire biotech industry. It’s constantly buzzing thanks to the numerous bars, restaurants and food trucks. In Lake Union Park, along the water sits the Museum of History & Industry which highlights the city’s history as well as business and innovation. Locals often head out to the lake for boating and paddle boarding. This neighborhood is also the home of Denny Park, which is the oldest green space in the city. To access other parts of the city from here, simply hop on the streetcar.
host_about:
We’re Blueground, a global proptech company with several thousand move-in-ready apartments in a growing number of major cities around the world. With flexible terms and homes in vibrant, centrally based neighborhoods, you’ll feel at home and free to roam for as long as you want — a month, a year, or longer. 

Each apartment is thoughtfully designed with exclusive furnishings, fully equipped kitchens, and incredible amenities – making every day a five-star experience. From day one, you’ll enjoy high-speed Wi-Fi, premium linens, and smart home entertainment. Plus, access to pools, gyms, and outdoor spaces in select buildings.

Why stress over your apartment? We provide a hassle-free alternative — a consistent, quality guest experience that starts even before you arrive. Because we let you book our most up-to-date apartment listings online, confirm with a click, pay securely, and check in easily. 

Even better? You can enhance your stay with car rentals, grocery delivery, laundry services, and more through our special partnerships. 

During your stay
Upon arrival, you’ll either be greeted personally by a Blueground team member or given self-check-in instructions. The entire apartment is yours! You’ll enjoy reliable support via email, phone, and our Guest App, where you can request everything from a home cleaning to extra towels. 

We’ll share all details upon confirmation of your stay.

name: Stunning Urban Loft in Historic Downtown Seattle
description:
This spacious, 730 SF loft boasts newly refinished wood floors, 14 foot ceilings, large windows, exposed brick walls and original beams. Beautifully and comfortably furnished with one-of-a kind pieces and decor, fully stocked kitchen (cookware, dishes, utensils, etc.), and large bathroom.

One lofted queen-sized bed can sleep two. Full-sized futon is available for a third guest.
neighborhood_overview: Pioneer Square is the charming, bustling historic district in downtown Seattle. The neighborhood features some of Seattle's prized architecture, cobblestone alleyways, and a great gallery and restaurant scene. It's centrally located and within walking distance to the stadiums and most popular destinations downtown. Please note that there are a few homeless shelters and missions in the area, as is common in many urban neighborhoods. However, we have never had any issues with resident or guest safety--in fact, most praise our building's location--and Pioneer Square is considered to be a very safe part of Seattle. For those prospective guests who are averse to seeing homeless people or panhandlers, we suggest choosing an accommodation outside of downtown Seattle.

host_about:
Hello travelers,
I live in the expensive part of Seattle and am trying to makeup the downtown living by sharing my house with you. I have all the basics taken care of and strive to provide my guests with a clean and comfortable place to sleep. Please don't expect it to be a hotel service and please don't expect that I am the only person in the house, opening up the entire house up for you.
By nature I am kind, responsible, quiet, friendly and easy going. I love to be around people. I am looking to host kind and friendly females and friends. The original spirit of Airbnb (if you know the founding story) is dead now with commercialization. I am looking to revive it and foster trust and acquaintanceship, sharing experiences what not, just like hanging over with a friend. If that’s not you and you like to keep to yourself that’s fine by me as well.
Please let me know in advance if you have any special requirements. I will do my best to accomodate your requests!
Don’t get me into trouble and enjoy yourselves, I am always here with any tips and tricks of the town!
If you are booking an airbnb for the first time use my link booGPTKIB0 to get $40 credit

*Luxury Hotels Meet Vacation Rentals*

It's great to meet you! We're Recreation Vacation Rentals, a vacation rental management company based in Seattle, but we manage vacation homes throughout the US.

We were founded by two former hotel executives with the goal of bringing the same practices and processes from some of the best hotels in the world to the vacation rental industry to improve consistency and guest experience.

We take what you love about hotels and what you appreciate about vacation rentals and bring them together into one perfect stay. 

We love the hospitality industry and can't wait to welcome you to one of our homes. Our team is here for you throughout your stay, ready to help with anything.

neighborhood_overview:
Pike Place Market in downtown Seattle is a vibrant and iconic destination for both locals and visitors. Nestled along the waterfront, it offers a dynamic blend of dining, shopping, and cultural experiences. Spanning over 9 acres, the Market is a bustling hub featuring the original Starbucks, the famous fishmongers with their fish-tossing tradition, historic buildings, and independent businesses. Whether you're exploring artisanal goods, grabbing a bite to eat, or soaking up the lively atmosphere, Pike Place Market showcases the best of Seattle’s charm.

Stroll through downtown and discover nearby cultural highlights, including the Seattle Art Museum, Dimitriou's Jazz Alley, and the Seattle Great Wheel. With its variety of on-site restaurants, Starbucks and Locust Brewing Co. just steps away, and easy access to highways and transit, this neighborhood is an ideal base for exploring Seattle.

Downtown is Seattle's primary shopping district, waterfront, Pike Place Market, and business central. Downtown is compact compared to other West Coast cities, so it's easy to walk everywhere. The western part of First Hill, where you'd be staying, is a wonderful, prime, sub-neighborhood within Downtown and adjacent to hip Capitol Hill.

On a map, it looks like the building is adjacent to the freeway, but freeways run under the city near the building, making it easier to walk the downtown neighborhood than it looks on a map.

We're a block east of the Central Business District that includes the Convention Center, a 7-minute walk from the Westlake Light rail link to/from the airport, a block south of the Pike/Pine Corridor which encompasses the retail shopping core, and a block west of Capitol Hill, Seattle's popular district for nightlife and entertainment. neighborhood_overview:
Queen Anne Hill is a beautiful urban neighborhood just minutes from downtown Seattle.

Most of the homes here are beautiful Craftsman style homes (ours was built in 1913), that many neighbors take great pride in maintaining the original quality of.

We provide a few books that will help you navigate the hill to take advantage of the many walks and scenic views we have here... we are GREEN most of the year and many flowers stay "flowery" to enjoy all season. Though spring and summer of course they all start showing off - always stop and smell the roses.

You are 3 minute drive or 10-15 minute walk to the top of the hill to enjoy coffee shops, local boutiques, and many restaurants.

There is a local Wholefoods and Safeway 7 mins from the house for your grocery needs as well as a convenient store on the corner of 6th & McGraw.

We’re Blueground, a global proptech company with several thousand move-in-ready apartments in a growing number of major cities around the world. With flexible terms and homes in vibrant, centrally based neighborhoods, you’ll feel at home and free to roam for as long as you want — a month, a year, or longer.

Why stress over your apartment? We provide a hassle-free alternative — a consistent, quality guest experience that starts even before you arrive. Because we let you book our most up-to-date apartment listings online, confirm with a click, pay securely, and check in easily.

During your stay
Upon arrival, you’ll either be greeted personally by a Blueground team member or given self-check-in instructions. The entire apartment is yours! You’ll enjoy reliable support via email, phone, and our Guest App, where you can request everything from a home cleaning to extra towels.

neighborhood_overview:
Anchored by the University of Washington’s leafy campus, this youthful neighborhood offers international dining and eclectic shopping.

Explore
Two highlights of visiting U-Dub’s verdant campus are exploring the amazing collections of fossils, Northwest Indigenous art, and cultural artifacts at the beautifully designed Burke Museum (H4303 Memorial Way NE) and viewing the impressive contemporary art collection at the Henry Art Gallery (H15th Ave NE & NE 41st St). For a relaxing walk or a pleasant picnic amid lush greenery, head to peaceful Ravenna Park (5520 Ravenna Ave NE).

Eat and Drink
In a romantic storefront space, Pancita (5501 30th Ave NE) serves artful modern Mexican fare, while longtime favorites Taste of India (5517 Roosevelt Way NE) and Thai Tom (4543 University Way NE) continue to polish U District’s reputation for authentic, affordable international fare. Xi’an Noodles (5259 University Way NE) draws legions of fans for savory biang biang nood

host_about:
I am from China and have lived in the US for 16 years. I have been fortunate to build up a group of close friends who believed in me. They say I am kind, loyal, reliable, and fun to be with. I cannot imagine life without my friends. They are the foundation on which I have built my life. I am a runner and like all outdoor activities. I love to travel when I can. 各位租客大家好！我来自中国，现在在美国生活了16年。我很幸运地结交了一群信任我的好朋友，她们说我善良，忠诚，可靠，热情，开朗，有趣。我有进取的心，有似水的梦怀，有崇高的理想。  我，幽默宽容。不喜欢看别人满面怒容的样子，我认为微笑才是天下最美的风景。“比大地宽阔的是海洋，比海洋宽阔的是天空，比天空宽阔的是人的心灵。”  我，积极进取。小小的我是一粒沙，但不甘于落后，一生庸碌无为。我，爱好跑步，热爱旅行，非常喜欢户外运动，渴望把生活中的美好事物分享给身边的朋友。比起旅行，我更加喜欢去学习当地的文化，了解他们的生活。我作为房东，在我的住宿里，我一定尽我所能为您提供一切便利，使您的旅行更加轻松愉快。感谢您驻留在我这里……

name: Seattle Cloud Room
description:
Your private room is located in my historic hotel built in 1904, large hallways, full shared kitchen, private mini fridge in your room and 3 shared bathrooms (see reviews)
Our building is a large beautiful building with an interesting history (ask if your curious)
We have a free parking lot, restaurants downstairs and lots of fun things to do within feet of our building. I am very accessible but give you space as you need. We are are located above a bar so its not great for light sleepers
neighborhood_overview:
Located by King county international airport and 15 minutes bus to Downtown. Visiting this area you will get the feeling of Seattle's original grunge scene with planes trains and automobiles and LOTS of places to eat and drink. Our building has two lounges ,a pool hall downstairs and the Georgetown trailer park mall opens in our parking lot on weekends. We are housed in a historic 1904 hotel which has been converted lovingly to host artists studios and your airbnb room. This building is in the middle of a hopping part of town so do not expect cricket quiet (not for light sleepers). Although your room is mostly quiet space sometimes you may hear an airplane or music from downstairs. We provide earplugs and white noise machines for the more you if you need. (read reviews) This is a great place to start your Seattle adventure . We look forward to meeting you and making your stay awesome.
A little grit, and allot of love have resurrected this neighborhood and arts community. Easy
host_about:
I am a visual artist who is  the  director of a community  Arts Center, art studios and guest rooms co-mingle to create a fun experience if you choose. Original art lines the hallways and some of the rooms  of our space, which is a restored Hotel and we welcome all including non artists with open arms. Not Arty at all? that's ok we are also close to stadiums, downtown,  nature  (Kubota Gardens, the arboretum, Seward Park, Alki Beach, Lincoln Park, Schmitz Park,  and yep golfing options (West Seattle and Jefferson Park both have awesome courses). We are also located up the street from the Boeing Flight museum and school , Northwest Institute of Asian and Oriental medicine (NIAOM) and also   The School of Acrobatics and Circus arts (SANCA) and not far away from Fed Ex and Amazon downtown.

Are you a foodie ???
We have soooo many amazing restaurants in the area (South Park, Georgetown  Beacon hill and White Center ) of course down town also but if you want to spread the  love in the neighborhood then just look at my guide book (south Seattle's finest)  

Our Space
---------------
Our space is hard to describe but we have been compared to a scrappy McMenamin's We have a large space but very clean and magical ( built as a hotel in 1904) our historical building has been lovingly restored .
We are not your usual space so please read carefully... think old school hotel / European hostel without the ghosts....or maybe there are ghosts you will have to see (wink wink) No ghosts that  are too precocious I promise :)
We have three shared and very clean bathrooms
One very well stocked kitchen (pots, pans, dishes and the like provided) 
And if you enjoy a morning coffee or tea / or evening glass of wine (or smoke) we have a very expansive back porch with couches , tables and a designated smoking area (New Orleans meets Georgetown)

 If you are sick please do not travel.  I'm a fairly warm person, i like to give hugs but currently I am keeping social distancing and ask that if you visit us that you do also.  
About Me 
I LOVE LOVE LOVE being a host, traveling and meeting awesome people. I have recently adopted a little girl doggie named Pickles who is sweet and learning how to greet people, she came all the way from Mexico but is not traumatized at all, if you are allergic to dogs then please let me know before hand so i can have her in my office.   
 The building is truly a magical charmer and  I think you will enjoy your stay here

Special things to be aware of
* I follow Airbnb’s enhanced cleaning protocol, which was developed with expert guidance.


***Please note that the rooms are on the second floor and we unfortunately are not ADA accesible. 

***Also of note our space is in the city so it's active and not always cricket quiet some noise from events , street or airplanes may happen, if you need a super quiet space book a hotel in the country. Most of the time the building itself is quiet but we have planes that fly overhead and a hopping building with fun restaurants and a pool hall downstairs. 

HANDS ON / only one staff member / so please be communicative
 I only have one staff member and do all cleaning, booking and greeting (except evening arrivals) myself so it is appreciated that you let me know your arrival time (as close as possible) at the time of your booking request and communicate this when you book if possible. I greet you in person or our evening manager if your arrival is after 6 pm 
***After 10 pm arrivals \late arrivals will require a $20 hr surcharge**. Late arrivals  with prior arrangement may be accepted) please inform me of your arrival time at the time of your booking request. Of course we know that emergencies happen ( delayed flights are real) and will work with you to make sure you are safe and respected

About ME
   I am an artist , entrepreneur and lover of people, plants and four legged beings. Sadly we can not allow animals in the rooms at this time unless they are a documented service animal with a vets authorization (must provide before booking)
   I  easy going person and  always try to keep our space filled with good energy. We welcome all respectful people here, this is a safe space. 
* please be vaccinated so we may keep everyone safe. Currently we are not requiring masking or social distancing in shared spaces , but you may do what ever makes you comfortable and please if you are immunocompromised just let us know and we will also wear our masks for you. Just let us know.


WANT TO GET MARRIED WHILE YOUR HERE?
  Well we have a wedding chapel on our property called Shotgun ceremonies
 ( you can find online) if ya wanna get hitched while your here. :) 
The lovely officiant of Shotgun ceremonies can work with you on a wedding package ( and yes Elvis can be present ) believe it!!
( I am not  the officiant...so please do not ask me about setting up the details ) but if you book thru her then you can also organize your guests rooms with me,
If you organize  / coordinate  to rent ALL the rooms in our space (There are 8 room), I will give you a 10% off the total (one point of contact only please for simplicity)  
****Please no non Airbnb guests onsite unless they are helping you with your luggage , or help up and down stairs

****NO SMOKING of anything inside BUILDING / NO VAPING/
 …you can do all these things in our Smoking area outside. I  am easily accessible if you need anything, I am happy to oblige most requests and strive to make every traveler feel welcome  but I also will give you your space. I try to take Sundays off to rest and have time with my dog. (Dog lives off site )
I am also happy to  help you plan a fun day here in Seattle.  I have allot of travel info and happy to give you any recommendations . 


We look forward to meeting you and making your stay awesome!

To earn more about our community of Just search Georgetown Seattle
My life motto
"Life is short, art is long"

neighborhood_overview:
First Hill is a neighborhood in Seattle, Washington, United States. It is named for the hill on which it is located, which in turn is so named for being the first hill encountered while traveling east from downtown Seattle toward Lake Washington. First Hill is bounded on the west by Interstate 5, beyond which is Downtown, on the north by E. Pike and E. Madison Streets, beyond which is Capitol Hill, and on the south by Yesler Way, beyond which is the International District. The City of Seattle provides conflicting information about its eastern limit, beyond which are Cherry Hill and the Central District. Some describe it as being bounded by Broadway and Boren Avenues,[1] while others describe it as being bounded by 12th Avenue.[2]

The neighborhood's Scandinavian roots are still visible in its annual festivals and events, celebrating Ballard's heritage. host_about:
Seattle Vacation Home is the small family business of Lynne and Andy.  We have been hosting visitors to Seattle in more than 50 homes for over 7 years.  Seattle Vacation Home provides professional quality furnished housing with a personal touch. We offer exceptional value to our visitors by providing high-end accommodations at a reasonable price. We treat our teammates with respect by working in a partnership model and offering above-market pay. We are thoughtful about our impact on our neighbors, our environment, and the city of Seattle.

From Lynne and Andy: We are passionate about travel, having visited over 70 countries around the world... on all 7 continents!  While we enjoy a fancy hotel now and then, nothing beats the comforts of a real HOME away from home.  Especially now that we travel with our two young children!

This passion for travel has led us to build Seattle Vacation Home, a collection of more than 50 homes in Seattle that are an example of all the best traits we have found in our vacation rentals.  Whether you are coming to Seattle for vacation, business, relocation, medical treatment, a cruise, a wedding or any other reason, we promise you a fantastic stay with Seattle Vacation Home.

name: Gaslight Inn - Room 104
description:
The Gaslight Inn is centrally located in the Capitol Hill Neighborhood. Less than 5 minute walk to shops restaurants and Cap Hill Light Rail Station.

Room 104 is the original master bedroom suite, located on the 2nd floor and in the front of the house. Naturally, its larger than most of our other guest rooms including a spacious sitting room with a large natural gas fireplace with comfy club chairs, queen size bed and private bathroom.
neighborhood_overview: Diverse Capitol Hill is packed with hip bars, eateries and gay clubs, plus laid-back coffee shops and indie stores. description:
If you're seeking a unique space in an urban setting, look no further! This beautiful, spacious loft offers super high ceilings, large windows, natural wood floors, and all the amenities you'll need during your stay in Seattle. Located in the heart of Pioneer Square, right next to a waterfall park, you'll be steps away from multiple restaurants, boutiques, museums, and the light rail station.

neighborhood_overview: Pioneer Square is the charming, bustling historic district in downtown Seattle and our building, The Lucknow, is a historic property which is listed on the national register of historic locations. The neighborhood features some of Seattle's prized architecture, cobblestone alleyways, and a great gallery and restaurant scene. It's centrally located and within walking distance to the stadiums and most popular destinations downtown. Please note that there are a few homeless shelters and missions in the area, as is common in many urban neighborhoods. However, we have never had any issues with resident or guest safety--in fact, most praise our building's location--and Pioneer Square is considered to be a very safe part of Seattle. For those prospective guests who are averse to seeing homeless people or panhandlers, we suggest choosing an accommodation outside of downtown Seattle.

description:
Located in Seattle’s University District neighborhood, this newly appointed two bedroom apartment features a unique and unsurpassed location and property details in which you surely will delight.

This property is located an ideal distance from the University of Washington and all its sport facilities (just blocks), Downtown Seattle (moments by car, UBER, bus, or light rail), and near countless restaurants, bars, shops, movie theaters, museums, coffeehouses, and other activities.
neighborhood_overview:
LOCATION
This property is located an ideal distance from the University of Washington and all its sport facilities (just blocks), Downtown Seattle (just moments by car, cab, or bus), and near countless other activities and points of interests. Right on the border between the University District and Ravenna neighborhoods, there are countless restaurants, bars, shops, movie theaters, museums, coffeehouses, and places to participate in outdoor activities mere moments from stepping out the apartment's door. host_about: I am a Seattle attorney. This area holds a special place in my heart as both a University of Washington alumni and someone who has spent over a decade living and exploring Seattle and the the incredible Fremont neighborhood. I love the energy and diversity of the people and activities Fremont shares with all those who visit. Whether it is shopping and strolling through the many lovely Fremont shops, having a picnic in Gas Works Park or Woodland Park Zoo, browsing the Farmer's Market on every Sunday morning, taking a walk along Lake Union and down the Burke Gilman Trail on a beautiful summer day, or just sitting and relaxing at one of the countless local cafes or bars - there is always something to do, to taste, and always another reason to live and stay in the Fremont neighborhood. I hope you will join me so that I may share my love for this area, Seattle, and the State of Washington as a whole. Safe travels and I hope to see you soon.

Capitol Hill is the artsy, quirky, vibrant gay-borhood of Seattle. You will find visionary creatives alongside nerdy techies and bedazzled performers all mixing next to each other in the cafes and streets of Capitol Hill. name: Standard Room C Historic Panama Hotel in Japantown
description: The Panama Hotel was built in 1910 and is rich in history. Through the years it has served as a home for generations of immigrants, fisherman and travelers. The building houses the only remaining Japanese bathhouse left in the US. The hotel is centrally located in Seattle's International District, close to downtown and is featured in the novel, "Hotel on the Corner of Bitter and Sweet." The single room standard has a full bed, antique lamp, night stand, sitting chair, dresser, closet, and sink.
neighborhood_overview: The Panama Hotel is located on a hill in Seattle's International District (Japantown). There is a large public paid parking lot next door, as well as paid street parking on the street in front of the hotel (free 8pm-8am, Sundays, holidays). There are many local stores, restaurants, and markets within easy walking distance as well as bus and street car public transportation options.
host_about: We work in e-commerce and media - our work often takes us traveling for business, and we love meeting other travelers while on a trip or hosting, and really enjoy discovering local customs in eating and drinking. We believe staying with or at locals is the best way to understand the world and enjoy life - don't hesitate to hit us up for tips about things to do while in town! Local history, design, and vintage homes (architecture and interior design) are interests of ours.

name: Belvidere Cabana - Seattle/Cascade Mtn Views
description: Perfectly situated to provide a short walk to the Admiral neighborhood or Alaska Junction, you have all of the benefits of city living at your back door. The 3-story home has a view of Cascade mountains and open floor plan and vaulted ceiling for the dining, living and kitchen area to maximize every inch of it's 800sq feet. Custom white washed planked flooring, wave-like tile work and ocean hues of light blue, gray and driftwood give one the sense that you are visiting a coastal cottage.
neighborhood_overview: The best thing about this part of West Seattle is it's proximity to everything! The "Junction" is a two block main street and the hub of the community. It's a 1-min drive or 10 minute walk to an eclectic mix of restaurants, bars, boutiques and shopping. The host favorites are Husky Deli for homemade ice cream, watching the sports events at any bar along Alki Beach and walking at low tide or having a bonfire at a dusk, taking the water taxi across the bay to the Seattle downtown waterfront, classic Italian at Il Nido or running the trails at Lincoln Park and beach boardwalk.
host_about:
I have lived in Seattle all of my life and wouldn't live anywhere else. I tried! After living/working abroad and seeing other countries, I realized our "Emerald City" is where I belong. I went to culinary school and love to share that passion with our guests. I currently work independently and stay at home with our two young children. 

We can't live without things to do which is everything the Pacific NW has to offer AND within easy reach! We can go clam-digging just outside our neighborhood or in 45 minutes find ourselves  skiing at Snoqualmie Pass. 

My husband David (a California transplant) has been a Seattleite for over  22 years and obviously loves it here! He has  been with the Seattle Fire Department for 19 years and cherishes what he does. We both  coach youth sports for the YMCA and WSSC and cherish spending time with our family. 
We believe the Pacific NW's best kept secret is:  It really doesn't rain as much as they say! Everything that surrounds you... the city, mountains and water are just absolutely transcending! Our summers here are bar-none with the most spectacular long days of sunlight.

neighborhood_overview: Seattle’s closest beach Alki is a Pacific Northwestern riff on the popular beaches of Southern California. Along this two-mile stretch of beach, you’ll find a fair number of volleyball courts, ample tidepooling opportunities, as well as a handful of restaurants, bars, and cafes perfect for a visit any time of day. Alki Beach is an ideal spot on a sunny day in Seattle. description: Welcome to Queen Anne! Put the perfect touch on your visit to Seattle by lodging in a neighborhood named for its standout architecture. This tasteful, modern home accommodates 8 guests with 4 bedrooms and 3 full bathrooms. You’ll be thrilled with quick access to downtown and Seattle's most memorable sights, but you’ll also enjoy luxury living, complete with a rooftop deck, garage parking, and 3 stories of incredible natural light streaming through enormous windows!
neighborhood_overview:
Queen Anne is one of the most iconic neighborhoods in Seattle for good reason! It is home to the Space Needle, runs along the beautiful shore of Lake Union, and is home to some of Seattle’s most beautiful historic homes and timeless architecture. In Queen Anne, you’ll soak in the most memorable views of the city — the glistening waters of Puget Sound and the rugged peaks of the Olympic Range and Mount Rainier are some of the most notable highlights. Take a walk over to Kerry Park (AKA, the Queen Anne Hill) for some of the best cliffside viewing of the rugged Pacific Northwest and a stroll around manicured gardens and lush landscapes.

Queen Anne also offers more urban sightseeing than any visitor could fit into a day! Check out the observation deck of the Space Needle ($25 per person) for panoramic views of the region, take the monorail to the shopping districts, go boating on Lake Union, or take a walk along Westlake Ave. to see the houseboats. neighborhood_overview:
Highland Park is a diverse working class neighborhood in West Seattle. You'll find quiet, tree-lined streets with modest homes and a few small apartment buildings. There's not much in the way of entertainment or dining in the neighborhood, but you're not far from hubs like West Seattle Junction and Downtown Seattle.

For recreation you've got the 8.4 acre (3.4 hectare) Westcrest Park, which features open fields, playgrounds, picnic areas, and an off-leash area for dogs.

The neighborhood has easy access to two major highways so commuting south of the city is a breeze.

Highland Park is bordered on the north by Riverview, on the east by South Park, on the south by White Center, and on the west by South Delridge.

description: New spacious 2 bedroom unit close to everything!  Enjoy your home away from home in one of the best neighborhoods in Seattle - Queen Anne. neighborhood_overview: There are tons of cool local restaurants and bars in the neighborhood of Queen Anne.  Uptown Espresso, Ozzie’s Karaoke Bar,  and Buckley’s sports-themed bar.  If this neighborhood had a central nervous system, Queen Anne Avenue would be the spinal cord; it runs straight through the middle and is where most of the important stuff happens. Up at the top of the hill, there are about 10 blocks’ worth of unique and charming places to peruse. Though there are great places to nosh—Queen Anne coffee company, the famous How to Cook a Wolf, or Betty—there are many other things to do! Check out the stellar view of downtown Seattle and Mount Rainier from Kerry Park. Or relax and play a board game before you buy it at Blue Highway Games.

name: Blueground | Bell Town, rooftop, nr top dining
description: Feel at home wherever you choose to live with Blueground. You’ll love this roomy Belltown furnished one bedroom apartment with its modern decor, fully equipped kitchen, and exquisite living room with great views. Ideally located, you’re close to all the best that Seattle has to offer! (ID #SEA661)
neighborhood_overview: This furnished apartment is located in walkable Belltown. With an enviable proximity to the water, you will also find yourself striding distance to Amazon’s HQ, Pike Place, Denny Triangle and Lower Queen Anne. Belltown itself has no shortage of sushi bars, java joints and nightlife options concentrated along 1st and 2nd Avenues. Connect yourself to the rest of the city with local buses, the South Lake Union Streetcar and the area’s protected bike lanes. Runners will love starting their jog at the Olympic Sculpture Park as the Elliott Bay Trail extends northwards.
host_about:
We’re Blueground, a global proptech company with several thousand move-in-ready apartments in a growing number of major cities around the world. With flexible terms and homes in vibrant, centrally based neighborhoods, you’ll feel at home and free to roam for as long as you want — a month, a year, or longer. 

Each apartment is thoughtfully designed with exclusive furnishings, fully equipped kitchens, and incredible amenities – making every day a five-star experience. From day one, you’ll enjoy high-speed Wi-Fi, premium linens, and smart home entertainment. Plus, access to pools, gyms, and outdoor spaces in select buildings.

Why stress over your apartment? We provide a hassle-free alternative — a consistent, quality guest experience that starts even before you arrive. Because we let you book our most up-to-date apartment listings online, confirm with a click, pay securely, and check in easily. 

Even better? You can enhance your stay with car rentals, grocery delivery, laundry services, and more through our special partnerships. 

During your stay

neighborhood_overview:
Located just off the West Seattle Bridge, the Luna Park neighborhood of West Seattle was once home to the famous Luna Park amusement park, known as the Coney Island of the West that operated from 1907 until 1913.

With its hand-carved carousel, Figure Eight Roller Coaster, Cave of Mystery, 2 theaters, Dancehall, and both fresh and saltwater swimming pools, it was a sight to behold. Plus it had the longest and best-stocked bar in Elliott Bay.

Eventually, a climate of moralism against "boozers from Seattle" invading the area and a series of political scandals contributed to Luna Park's demise, and it closed forever in 1913.

The Luna Park Cafe is named in its honor and is just steps away. The cafe has great food, beer, a working jukebox and other curios, and plenty of historical pictures of the amusement park in its heyday.

Transportation is easy, with the Rapid Ride bus (every 10 minutes) that goes either to South Lake Union in Seattle, the Ala

I started hosting on Airbnb in 2017 and immediately knew this was for me. Guests kept raving about their stays and I loved every minute of it. I became a Superhost since first eligible, and haven’t looked back.  I wanted to do more.

In 2018 I started my company, HOST JEEVES, to manage investment/vacation properties for other owners. It’s been great so far.

As your host, I will do everything to ensure you have an amazing experience. Please come and be my guest for a truly memorable stay!

description: Stay in a recently renovated two bedroom apartment in the lower level of a historic home in the Wallingford/Fremont neighborhoods of Seattle. neighborhood_overview:
Wallingford and Fremont are two of Seattle's most vibrant and sought-after neighborhoods, and they offer a unique blend of urban charm and natural beauty. Wallingford is a peaceful and residential area that boasts beautiful tree-lined streets, parks, and a bustling commercial district filled with restaurants, shops, and cafes.

Fremont, on the other hand, is a quirky and eclectic neighborhood that has earned the nickname "The Center of the Universe." Here, visitors can explore the famous Fremont Troll, a large sculpture under the bridge, visit local art galleries and shops, and enjoy some of Seattle's best craft breweries.

Both neighborhoods are within easy walking distance of each other, making it easy for visitors to experience the best of both worlds. Whether you're looking for a peaceful getaway or a lively urban adventure, Wallingford and Fremont are the perfect places to call home during your visit to Seattle.

description: Location !   Downtown & Pike Pl Market: 20-30 minute walk;  Capitol Hill is a 10-15 minutes walk.  Comfortable home on tree lined side street of Pike/Pine.  Multitude of cafes, bars, and the best book store in Seattle. Also see our Bedroom #1.
neighborhood_overview:
We've watched as our 'hood (Pike/Pine) has become a mecca for food, drink, and art. We have nationally recognized restaurants and bars (as well as numerous food trucks) within blocks. Music venues, and theaters allow for an exciting night life. Many coffee houses, interesting retail, and the best book store in Seattle keep the days interesting. The Seattle International Film Festival and the NW Film Forum both have local theaters with daily showings of indie films. We also have Central Co-op, a great place to shop for local and organic foods.

Our neighborhood has a great diversity of people. Capitol Hill (just north of Pike/Pine) has been the city's gayborhood for years; Pike/Pine has been home to many of Seattle's arts community, visual, dance, theater; and Seattle University is just two blocks away.

We live on a side street of homes from the early 1900's with several older brick apartment buildings mixed in. Its relaxed and low-key, a great place to walk a
host_about:
Louis: I've been around the block a few times, and do my best to have fun each time.  I've been in Seattle 20+ years, and I love it.  I also love getting my hands in the dirt…… I garden for a living, helping clients keep their yards looking good.  And when a house is going on the market, I will come in and 'stage' the yard, making it look its best.  Kevin and I have been together forever.  We enjoy hanging out with friends and family and the occasional road trip.

Kevin: I'm a West Coast boy, born in Seattle, college in LA, San Francisco in the 80's, and back to Seattle.  Love it here.  Through being self employed (book keeping, minor remodeling) and doing our version of home improvement (our house is always "in process"), we've managed to put together a fun, kind of odd-ball life that we enjoy.  I have really enjoyed meeting our guests - so many different people living different sorts of lives, and having such a range of interests.

description:

neighborhood_overview:
Phinney Ridge and Ballard are both famous and unique neighborhoods. There are tons of coffee shops, restaurants, and things to see and do in the area, including farmers markets, sightseeing, pub crawls, parks, beaches, and walks. You'll be staying right between the two neighborhoods in a quiet, relaxing, and safe family-friendly area, yet close enough to go out and have some fun in the town.

Just a 10 minute drive south and west are Fremont and downtown Ballard which have plenty of nightlife, bars, and on Sundays, a market of farmers and craftspeople. 15 minutes to downtown Seattle and just a quick drive away for a day-trip to the mountains or the islands!

Don't forget to check out the Barking Dog Alehouse across the street. Bring the growler we provide along, and you will get 1 free regular draft beer fill of the growler, as well as 10% off with your meal purchase.

If you're in the mood for a movie and can't find what you're looking for on Netflix, TV,
host_about:
I grew up abroad in a multicultural world. I love diversity. I think it makes the world a better place. Naturally, meeting new interesting people is very exciting to me. There is so much to learn from each other.

After finishing college I began working as a software engineer on video editing software and have been doing that for the past 10+ years. In the intersection between science and art, I am most at home when form meets function in the most elegant ways. It is so exciting to be able to watch a movie and know exactly how it is made, right down the each pixel. If you're interested in this sort of thing, I love chatting about it-- but be forewarned, you may never be able to watch a movie the same way. The magic of film-making can sometimes go away when you know how it works.

As an engineer, I absolutely love fixing things and tinkering. Naturally, I spent the past several years upgrading our home. I decided it would be great to share all the upgrades and hard work I've done and list it on Airbnb. It really has been a labor of love for me. My wife and I live nearby, so we're always close by if something breaks. I know the home inside and out and will do everything I can to make sure your stay is amazing. 

I love adventure! My wife and I met at a Lindy Hop dance, we've been scuba diving, skydiving, and I even have my very own paraglider. If you're an adventurous type too, I'd be happy to give you some ideas for things to do while you're visiting Seattle. I look forward to hosting you and chatting about interesting topics!

name: Lake Cabin
description: Unique in-city paradise on Playland at Bitter Lake. Offering 80 ft of waterfront living - enjoy the amazing flora and fauna and the tranquil setting. The property is an opportunity for bird watching, fishing, pedal boarding, and other lake activities with the convenience of being only 10 min away from Seattle and all amenities. Playland cabin a beautiful landscape with a BBQ, trampoline, pizza oven, fire pit, gas fireplace, covered patio, lake dock, big yard and Hot Tub.
neighborhood_overview: Bitter Lake played a more prominent role in Seattle at mid-20th century when it was not yet officially part of the city. From May 24, 1930 to 1961, it was home to Playland, one of several amusement parks built by the Washington Amusement Company. The Lake Cabin was build in 1924. Bitter Lake is named after its most notable feature, Bitter Lake. It was a mostly natural forest of Douglas-fir and Western Redcedar, inhabited by Native Americans, until the late 19th century. Development especially picked up when the Seattle-to-Everett Interurban streetcar reached the lake in 1906. A sawmill operated in the area until 1913, when most of the trees had been cut down.

neighborhood_overview: This furnished apartment is located in Lower Queen Anne, an up and coming neighborhood around the Seattle Center. The area is also referred to as Uptown by locals, especially in recent years. The Space Needle is just a few minutes' walk from Lower Queen Anne, as are the Pacific Northwest Ballet, the Seattle Children's Theatre, and the Museum of Pop Culture. The neighborhood is also home to the headquarters of the Seattle Post-Intelligencer as well as a thriving dining scene. You can find everything from fast-casual spots like local favorite Dick's Drive-in -- the Lower Queen Anne is the only Dick's location with seating -- to high-end, white tablecloth restaurants. Lower Queen Anne is connected to downtown by the Seattle Center monorail, and several bus lines serve the neighborhood.
host_about:
We’re Blueground, a global proptech company with several thousand move-in-ready apartments in a growing number of major cities around the world. With flexible terms and homes in vibrant, centrally based neighborhoods, you’ll feel at home and free to roam for as long as you want — a month, a year, or longer. 

Each apartment is thoughtfully designed with exclusive furnishings, fully equipped kitchens, and incredible amenities – making every day a five-star experience. From day one, you’ll enjoy high-speed Wi-Fi, premium linens, and smart home entertainment. Plus, access to pools, gyms, and outdoor spaces in select buildings.

Why stress over your apartment? We provide a hassle-free alternative — a consistent, quality guest experience that starts even before you arrive. Because we let you book our most up-to-date apartment listings online, confirm with a click, pay securely, and check in easily. 

Even better? You can enhance your stay with car rentals, grocery delivery, laundry services, and more through our special partnerships. 

During your stay
Upon arrival, you’ll either be greeted personally by a Blueground team member or given self-check-in instructions. The entire apartment is yours! You’ll enjoy reliable support via email, phone, and our Guest App, where you can request everything from a home cleaning to extra towels. 

We’ll share all details upon confirmation of your stay.

neighborhood_overview: This furnished apartment is located in Lower Queen Anne, an up and coming neighborhood around the Seattle Center. The area is also referred to as Uptown by locals, especially in recent years. The Space Needle is just a few minutes' walk from Lower Queen Anne, as are the Pacific Northwest Ballet, the Seattle Children's Theatre, and the Museum of Pop Culture. The neighborhood is also home to the headquarters of the Seattle Post-Intelligencer as well as a thriving dining scene. You can find everything from fast-casual spots like local favorite Dick's Drive-in -- the Lower Queen Anne is the only Dick's location with seating -- to high-end, white tablecloth restaurants. Lower Queen Anne is connected to downtown by the Seattle Center monorail, and several bus lines serve the neighborhood.

description: Welcome to our modern townhouse in South Seattle! Experience the perfect blend of comfort and convenience in this spacious 3-bed, 3.5-bath retreat. neighborhood_overview:
South Seattle, near the Othello Light Rail Station, is a vibrant and diverse neighborhood. With convenient access to public transportation, a variety of dining options, and community events, it's an engaging place to explore and experience.

In the area, you can find an array of international cuisines, reflecting the multicultural character of the neighborhood. From authentic eateries to trendy coffee shops, there's something to satisfy every palate.

For outdoor enthusiasts, there are several parks and green spaces nearby. Othello Playground (right across the street from the townhouse!) and Seward Park are popular spots for recreational activities, picnics, and community gatherings. These green areas provide a refreshing escape, allowing you to enjoy nature within the city limits.

And to explore other areas of Seattle, just hop on the light rail, which can bring you to the stadiums, downtown, or UW!

host_about:
Seattle Vacation Home is the small family business of Lynne and Andy.  We have been hosting visitors to Seattle in more than 50 homes for over 7 years.  Seattle Vacation Home provides professional quality furnished housing with a personal touch. We offer exceptional value to our visitors by providing high-end accommodations at a reasonable price. From Lynne and Andy: We are passionate about travel, having visited over 70 countries around the world... on all 7 continents!  While we enjoy a fancy hotel now and then, nothing beats the comforts of a real HOME away from home.  Especially now that we travel with our two young children!

Having rented countless vacation homes during our time, we have copious notes of what we do and don't like. name: Queen Anne Modern Home Free Parking |SLU| Gym
description:
Welcome to our stylish Queen Anne townhome with stunning Seattle skyline views. Situated in the unbeatable and safe Queen Anne neighborhood, you'll be minutes away from major attractions like the Space Needle, Chihuly Garden, QFC, and shops.

Unwind in the master suite upstairs, complete with vaulted ceilings, a walk-in closet, and a 5-piece bath. Our recently renovated home boasts new flooring and paint, making it the perfect comfortable home for your city stay. We can't wait to welcome you!
neighborhood_overview:
The neighborhood

Queen Anne is one of the safest neighborhoods in Seattle, providing you with peace of mind during your stay. Additionally, this neighborhood is situated close to all the major attractions Seattle has to offer. From the iconic Space Needle to the beautiful Chihuly Garden and Glass, you'll be just minutes away from all the action.
For those who are visiting Seattle for business, this location is also very close to SLU (South Lake Union), the Seattle Silicon Valley. Many of the biggest tech companies in the world are located here. So whether you're here for work or leisure, this vacation rental property is the perfect base for exploring everything Seattle has to offer.

✔ Museum of Pop Culture - 3 min drive
✔ South Lake Union – 4 min drive
✔ Woodland Park Zoo - 4 min drive
✔ Space Needle - 5 min drive
✔ Museum of History & Industry (MOHAI) – 5 min drive
✔ Chihuly Garden and Glass - 6 min drive
✔ University of W
host_about:
I love adventure and entrepreneurship. I have been to 23 different countries and living in 5 different cities for longer than 3 years. Currently, my wife and I live in the Seattle area with our little boy. We enjoy the water view, public parks, and the outdoors activities a lot and we would like to share all our favorite secret places to all other travelers, adventurers, and life lovers. We hope you enjoy Seattle as much as we do!

The next top 5 places to travel on my wish list.
(1) Antarctica
(2) Iceland
(3) Peru
(4) Egypt
(5) Rio

I also love basketball. I am a loyal Lakers fan for 20 years until Kobe Bryant retired. I love science fiction movie and start up a new business. I wish I can travel to 50 different countries before 50 and experience the world in a passionate way I love. 

My friend, glad to meet you in Airbnb and let's enjoy life in our own way!

name: Woodside Suite: Relax Amid Sea Breezes
description: Relax amid saltwater breezes at this cozy retreat near Puget Sound and one of Seattle’s most beautiful parks. Situated on a quiet residential street, Woodside Suite is a calming space, complete with a luxurious king-sized bed. Featuring a private entrance, the suite includes three rooms (including the bathroom) and occupies an entire floor of a house. A lush backyard awaits your picnic, or sit on the front porch and enjoy a view of the Sound and the Olympic Mountains.
neighborhood_overview: West Seattle is fast becoming one of Seattle’s hottest neighborhoods. It boasts Alki Beach (a long, sandy stretch with bike and walking paths leading to stunning views of downtown) and Lincoln Park (winding wooded trails lead to views of the islands and Olympics; we’ve spotted eagles, owls, and sea lions on our dog walks here; an outdoor saltwater pool is open to the public in the summer). Great restaurants abound in Morgan Junction, a short walk away, and the West Seattle Junction and Admiral District, both short drives.
host_about:
My husband and I have traveled the globe for work and leisure. We love the Pacific Northwest for its evergreen trees, mild four seasons and numerous bodies of water. And also for its countless wonderful restaurants, friendly people and good coffee. We are foodies and are constantly in search of the next restaurant.

When we are not eating we enjoy taking walks or runs in Lincoln Park by the Sound or kayaking on Seattle's many waterways.
 
We hope you enjoy your stay!

Revitalized Urban Village
In the 1970s, efforts to preserve Eastlake's character led to the 1999 Eastlake Neighborhood Plan, reflecting a community commitment to its heritage and charm.

Eclectic Architecture
Eastlake features a mix of houseboats, historic apartments, and modern homes. Its architectural diversity, from early 20th-century buildings to contemporary residences, adds to its unique character.

Parks and Recreation
Enjoy numerous lakeside street-end parks and green spaces like Rogers Playfield, part of the Olmsteds’ 1910 parks plan, ideal for relaxation and outdoor activities.

Perfect for Travelers
Eastlake offers business travelers a peaceful yet connected environment with easy access to downtown Seattle. Families will appreciate the friendly atmosphere and local shops, cafes, and restaurants along Eastlake Avenue.

description: Small groups will rest easy in my newly renovated Guest Suite. My house is centrally located in one of Seattle’s most charming and desirable neighborhoods. Walk along quaint, tree-lined streets to restaurants and shopping on Queen Anne Avenue or catch the bus a block away for a quick 10-minute ride to the popular Seattle Center and downtown. Afterwards, enjoy dinner or a glass of wine on the beautiful fenced-in outdoor patio or a soak in the warm swim spa.
host_about:
After my husband passed away, my daughter and I renovated our Queen Anne home. We renovated with the intentions of creating a Four Seasons Airbnb, hosting guests from all over the world, while we travel all over the world.  We added an additional floor, putting all the bedrooms on one floor. We opened up the main floor and built an amazing kitchen and living room. The dining room table seats eight, with kids seating for 6 close by! We turned the downstairs into a private Guest Suite. Our house was inspired by all the fabulous hotels we've stayed and ships we've sailed. We're calling our home the Queen Anne Oasis. Everything from the heated floors, towel warmers, and swim spa is the best. We want your visit to Queen Anne to be five stars all the way. 

The Queen Anne Oasis is for everyone, especially kids. My daughter created a game closet will all our favorite games. We've also left our bikes, scooters, and unicycles for our guests to use. 

My daughter and I are currently traveling, Queen Anne Oasis makes that possible. Throughout the house, you will see art that we've collected around the world and personal photos that tell our story. 

We'd love to host you on your visit to the Emerald City.

host_about:
Hi everyone and welcome to my city! I have lived here most of my life except for some time spent studying and working abroad in Germany. I also lived for a time in Ellensburg, in central WA State and Bellingham near the Canadian border studying. My educational background is in anthropology and german language. I really enjoy meeting people from all parts of the world and cultures. I also love to travel when possible! When I was in Germany I lived in West Berlin with an exiled East German family and I did lots of trips to the GDR which was one of the best experiences of my life.  I gained a new knowledge of how my country is viewed by another part of the world and made incredible friends that I still have decades later. 
Now I help people buy and sell homes to help them make big changes in their lives. It is a very rewarding career. And hosting with AirBnB is a way to meet many new people which is the next best thing to travelling! 
Also I love fixing up old houses and sometimes old cars and boats! I am quite the tinkerer so if you need some help fixing something on your trip please ask, ha!
Looking forward to meeting you,
Bobby

host_about:
Hey there! 

I am a professional AirBnB host and Lifestyle coach :-) I am originally from Illinois but have been living in Seattle since 2016. I am crazy about natural healthcare, rock climbing, salsa dancing, scuba diving and unconventional travel. Some of my favorite travel destinations so far have been Greece, Bali, Southern Thailand and the Galapagos. I also love road tripping around the U.S., only 7 more states I haven’t made it to yet!

AirBnB hosting has made a huge impact on my life. I love to share my space and to help others share their spaces with guests from all over the country and the world! I really love learning about the world through the stories of my guests. As a host, I am dedicated to creating a safe and comfortable home away from home. I look forward to meeting you!

neighborhood_overview: This furnished apartment is located in Downtown, the central business district of Seattle. It's the financial and commercial maritime hub as well as the center of shopping and nightlife. Numerous Fortune 500 companies are headquartered here, such as Nordstrom, Zillow, and Indeed. Local crafts and fresh produce are sold at the eclectic and vibrant Pike Place Market while dozens of skyscrapers overlook Elliott Bay to the West - part of Puget Sound, which leads to the Pacific Ocean. description: Elegant, airy and bright, this private townhouse sits back from the street on East Queen Anne. Vivid views over Ship Canal, Fremont & beyond. Great location & easy commute, ¼ mile to SPU, ½m to Alphabet, 2m to SLU. neighborhood_overview:
Queen Anne is an affluent neighborhood and geographic feature in Seattle, northwest of downtown. The neighborhood sits on the highest named hill in the city, with a maximum elevation of 456 feet (139 m). It covers an area of 7.3 square kilometers (2.8 sq mi), and has a population of about 28,000. Queen Anne is bordered by Belltown to the south, Lake Union to the east, the Lake Washington Ship Cana and Fremont to the north and Interbay to the west.
The neighborhood became a popular spot for the city's early economic and cultural elite to build their mansions, and the name derives from the architectural style typical of many of the early homes.
