description:
Need a Seattle beachfront staycation?

Unit 2 of this stylish triplex is right across the street from sandy Alki beach and offers sweeping 180° views. Enjoy the pleasures of the sand & surf!

Ride, scoot, paddleboard, volleyball, & bonfires are just outside your door.

neighborhood_overview:
Alki Beach is unique in Seattle. One of the few sandy beaches in the area, and perhaps the most popular beach in the summer. With plenty of shared bikes and scooters for rent, jogging/biking path, fire pits, picnic tables and a bathhouse/art studio, this beach is popular year-round.

Verdict: Alki Beach is awesome!

Plus, it is a Seattle City park, so the public has access. Most beaches in Washington State are classified as private property, so having this amazing beach park open to everyone is truly special.

Alki Beach Park is also part of the renowned "Whale Trail", a series of sites to view whales and other marine mammals from shore along the Pacific Coast. The best time to see orca whales from Alki is during the fall and winter, when the southern resident pods return to this area.

West Seattle itself is also a gem. The birthplace of modern Seattle, West Seattle has always had a small town vibe due to the fact that it is on the other side o
host_about:
I live in Alki Beach, West Seattle with my two daughters, Gabriela and Gina. We love Alki as it’s the closest thing to a beach boardwalk you can get in Seattle. 

Another place we love is Vashon Island (short ferry ride) where we lived for 10 years.  We also enjoy all the many parks, and spectacular water and mountains nearby. 

I started hosting on Airbnb in 2017 and immediately knew this was for me. Guests kept raving about their stays and I loved every minute of it. I became a Superhost since first eligible, and haven’t looked back.  I wanted to do more.

In 2018 I started my company, HOST JEEVES, to manage investment/vacation properties for other owners. It’s been great so far.

As your host, I will do everything to ensure you have an amazing experience. Please come and be my guest for a truly memorable stay!

Less than two blocks from the lake front park and a 2.8 mile loop trail, welcoming folks of all ages and abilities, and their dogs! neighborhood_overview:
The Green Lake neighborhood is located about 15 minutes North of Downtown Seattle.
A proud community of inviting local flair boasts an array of cafe's, coffee shops, fine restaurants, retail shopping, wellness services and other public conveniences.

Green Lake Park has a year round 2.8 mile waterfront walking trail and a 3.1 mile outer perimeter trail.
Non motorized water activities such as paddle boards and kayaks are permitted on the lake.
The park also has ball fields, sport courts, a designated shallow swimming area for children and a serene setting for picnics. And it's dog friendly!

Woodland Park Zoo is located nearby as well.

name: Victorian double room
description:
Making you comfortable is our priority, we hope you will enjoy a cozy and fun stay. This double room is an Amazing classy light filled room in our 1904 historic hotel. This bright and inviting room is a sweet room with a comfy full size bed
The main sleeping area contains a full size bed, side table, and soft lighting. Fresh linens, towels, washcloths provided. Second room has a mini fridge, fold down futon and a work desk
We can’t wait to host you, see you soon:)
neighborhood_overview:
The Georgetown area of Seattle is an eclectic arts and historical district with lots of fun things to do and also on a bus line 124 to easy 15 minute ride to downtown Seattle, Alki, Pike Place market , Space Needle and big wheel. We have a weekend bizarre market right out our back door filled with fun vintage finds.
A little grit, and allot of love have resurrected this neighborhood and arts community. Easy 15 minute bus ride to Pike Place Market, the Big Wheel, the waterfront parks and the Seattle Center and transportation to points beyond like Ballard locks, University district and Bellevue
#ClimatePledgeArena, #Lumenfield, #Seattlecenter, #PikePlaceMarket
#SeattleEroticArtsfestival, #Mariners, #Kraken , #CapitolHillBlockParty, #Pride, #SeattleInternationalFilmFestival, #MoistureFestival, #SeattleMaritimeFestival , #FreemontFair, #HonkFestWest, #Seafair, #BiteOfSeattle, #SeattleArtFair
host_about:
I am a visual artist who is  the  director of a community  Arts Center, art studios and guest rooms co-mingle to create a fun experience if you choose. Original art lines the hallways and some of the rooms  of our space, which is a restored Hotel and we welcome all including non artists with open arms. Not Arty at all? that's ok we are also close to stadiums, downtown,  nature  (Kubota Gardens, the arboretum, Seward Park, Alki Beach, Lincoln Park, Schmitz Park,  and yep golfing options (West Seattle and Jefferson Park both have awesome courses). We are also located up the street from the Boeing Flight museum and school , Northwest Institute of Asian and Oriental medicine (NIAOM) and also   The School of Acrobatics and Circus arts (SANCA) and not far away from Fed Ex and Amazon downtown.

Are you a foodie ???
We have soooo many amazing restaurants in the area (South Park, Georgetown  Beacon hill and White Center ) of course down town also but if you want to spread the  love in the neighborhood then just look at my guide book (south Seattle's finest)  

Our Space
---------------
Our space is hard to describe but we have been compared to a scrappy McMenamin's We have a large space but very clean and magical ( built as a hotel in 1904) our historical building has been lovingly restored .
We are not your usual space so please read carefully... think old school hotel / European hostel without the ghosts....or maybe there are ghosts you will have to see (wink wink) No ghosts that  are too precocious I promise :)
We have three shared and very clean bathrooms
One very well stocked kitchen (pots, pans, dishes and the like provided) 
And if you enjoy a morning coffee or tea / or evening glass of wine (or smoke) we have a very expansive back porch with couches , tables and a designated smoking area (New Orleans meets Georgetown)

 If you are sick please do not travel.  I'm a fairly warm person, i like to give hugs but currently I am keeping social distancing and ask that if you visit us that you do also.  
About Me 
I LOVE LOVE LOVE being a host, traveling and meeting awesome people. I have recently adopted a little girl doggie named Pickles who is sweet and learning how to greet people, she came all the way from Mexico but is not traumatized at all, if you are allergic to dogs then please let me know before hand so i can have her in my office.   
 The building is truly a magical charmer and  I think you will enjoy your stay here

Special things to be aware of
* I follow Airbnb’s enhanced cleaning protocol, which was developed with expert guidance.


***Please note that the rooms are on the second floor and we unfortunately are not ADA accesible. 

***Also of note our space is in the city so it's active and not always cricket quiet some noise from events , street or airplanes may happen, if you need a super quiet space book a hotel in the country. Most of the time the building itself is quiet but we have planes that fly overhead and a hopping building with fun restaurants and a pool hall downstairs. 

HANDS ON / only one staff member / so please be communicative
 I only have one staff member and do all cleaning, booking and greeting (except evening arrivals) myself so it is appreciated that you let me know your arrival time (as close as possible) at the time of your booking request and communicate this when you book if possible. I greet you in person or our evening manager if your arrival is after 6 pm 
***After 10 pm arrivals \late arrivals will require a $20 hr surcharge**. Late arrivals  with prior arrangement may be accepted) please inform me of your arrival time at the time of your booking request. Of course we know that emergencies happen ( delayed flights are real) and will work with you to make sure you are safe and respected

About ME
   I am an artist , entrepreneur and lover of people, plants and four legged beings. Sadly we can not allow animals in the rooms at this time unless they are a documented service animal with a vets authorization (must provide before booking)
   I  easy going person and  always try to keep our space filled with good energy. We welcome all respectful people here, this is a safe space. 
* please be vaccinated so we may keep everyone safe. Currently we are not requiring masking or social distancing in shared spaces , but you may do what ever makes you comfortable and please if you are immunocompromised just let us know and we will also wear our masks for you. Just let us know.


WANT TO GET MARRIED WHILE YOUR HERE?
  Well we have a wedding chapel on our property called Shotgun ceremonies
 ( you can find online) if ya wanna get hitched while your here. :) 
The lovely officiant of Shotgun ceremonies can work with you on a wedding package ( and yes Elvis can be present ) believe it!!
( I am not  the officiant...so please do not ask me about setting up the details ) but if you book thru her then you can also organize your guests rooms with me,
If you organize  / coordinate  to rent ALL the rooms in our space (There are 8 room), I will give you a 10% off the total (one point of contact only please for simplicity)  
****Please no non Airbnb guests onsite unless they are helping you with your luggage , or help up and down stairs

****NO SMOKING of anything inside BUILDING / NO VAPING/
 …you can do all these things in our Smoking area outside. I  am easily accessible if you need anything, I am happy to oblige most requests and strive to make every traveler feel welcome  but I also will give you your space. I try to take Sundays off to rest and have time with my dog. (Dog lives off site )
I am also happy to  help you plan a fun day here in Seattle.  I have allot of travel info and happy to give you any recommendations . 


We look forward to meeting you and making your stay awesome!

To earn more about our community of Just search Georgetown Seattle
My life motto
"Life is short, art is long"

name: Bamboo Room Historic Panama Hotel Seattle
description: The Panama Hotel was built in 1910 and is rich in history. Through the years it has served as a home for generations of immigrants, fisherman and travelers. The building houses the only remaining Japanese bathhouse left in the US. The hotel is centrally located in Seattle's International District, close to downtown and is featured in the novel, "Hotel on the Corner of Bitter and Sweet." neighborhood_overview:
Capital Hill is undeniably the Seattle's current coolest 'hood. It’s home to the city’s musicians and artists, counterculture mavens, and (for better or worse) flocks of yuppies attracted to the neighborhood’s unique spirit -- especially the dozens of bars, restaurants, music venues, and theaters that dot its landscape.

If you’re visiting Capitol Hill for the first time, it can be overwhelming, because there is so much to do. Capitol Hill is one of Seattle’s most popular neighborhoods. A hotspot of nightlife and restaurants, and the center of Seattle’s vibrant variety of independent shops, including one of the city’s largest bookstores. Just a few blocks north of the retail area, residents can find houses ranging from modest to grand. Capitol Hill has easy access to downtown as well as points north and south thanks to a light rail station in the heart of the neighborhood. neighborhood_overview:
Beacon Hill is a mellow bedroom neighborhood with a diverse ethnic history. The old Beacon Hill School building atop the hill has been renovated into a thriving community center with a food courtyard. It is just next to the light rail transit station, which requires you to descend 160 feet underground on an elevator to "catch the light rail". The area offers several restaurants, local pubs, along with the Red Apple grocery store, a bank, gas station, etc. There is also a library...and some new--mixed with old...plus plenty of nice pastry/coffee options.

The nearby Jimi Hendrix Park has the African American Museum, as well as soccer playing fields, basketball courts, and a great running route towards Lake Washington which allows for some hill work. The park currently has some construction as it will be the new entrance to the upcoming I-90 "East Link" Light rail station towards Bellevue.

If driving, this location also has easy access to I-90 Freeway towards th
host_about:
Travel, good ethnic food, waterfalls, hot springs, a nice book, and a glass of red wine.  I have traveled a lot internationally, and locally--so please let me know if you have an interest for Seattle, and I can point you in the right direction.

As to the place, I prefer clean and somewhat minimalist--yet still homey and functional.  The kitchen has a big movable island that begs for chopping vegetables, and I like creating conversational arrangements with furniture to encourage people to share their stories.

As a host, I tend to be hands off as oftentimes at work or running around, so texting via Airbnb is the best way to contact me if you need something.

The Box Art room facing Main St is adorned with delicate box art containing recreations of Asian scenery.

Step through the door of City Haven and immediately feel welcome inside a well-preserved Craftsman apartment. Many original architectural details remain, and these are enhanced by a careful selection of high-quality retro-chic fixtures and furnishings.

- Fully equipped, new chef's kitchen
- AC (air conditioning in Seattle? Yes!)
- secluded patio
- easy alley access with free, designated parking space
- spa bathroom with marble tile, rain head shower, deep tub
- one block to downtown express bus stop - no car needed!
- 7-12 min bus ride to explore Pike Place, Space Needle/other downtown destinations
- 3 blocks to grocery store
- walking distance to many restaurants, bars and coffee shops
- complimentary starter coffee and tea
- in-unit washer and dryer with complimentary laundry soap/dryer sheets
- hair dryer
- iron and ironing board
- complimentary soap, shampoo and conditioner dispenser in sh
neighborhood_overview: The apartment is in the Upper Fremont neighborhood. It's easily accessible to the Fremont, Green Lake, and Wallingford neighborhoods, and is just a 10-minute drive to downtown Seattle.

name: Beautiful West Seattle studio, close to Alki Beach
description:
From our West Seattle location, it is a 5-10 minute walk to Alki Beach, Admiral Theater, several nice restaurants and quaint coffee shops. The bus line at the end of our street will take you into downtown Seattle (Space Needle, Pike Place, Elliott Bay waterfront, Westlake Center) and the nearby football, soccer and baseball stadiums (all ~20 minute bus or car ride away).

We will make sure your visit with us is extra special, and we will help you plan your activities in our beautiful city.
neighborhood_overview:
Our house is located in a very friendly, very typical Seattle neighborhood, in a very convenient location to take advantage of all that Seattle has to offer.

There are three main areas of West Seattle - Alki Beach, Admiral Junction and the Alaska Junction.

Alki Beach is a close 10 minute walk down the hill, and is lovely to stroll around, plus visit shops and restaurants.

The Admiral Junction is also about a 10 minute easy walk away, and has restaurants and shops, as well as a renovated movie theater.

The Alaska Junction is the 'downtown' area of West Seattle, with lots of walking around shops and restaurants. It is the hub of West Seattle.
host_about: My wife is a Seattle area native and I have been here for over 30 years.  We have been in our current house for over 20 years, and love our location.  We have four kids, all of which are either in college or beyond.  Family and friends are very important to us.  Let us show you our beautiful city.

name: Awesome Studio In Heart of Seattle
description: Exceptional Studio in newer home, high end furnishings and bed located minutes from Arboretum, French Bakery, restaurants and bars. Mini Kitchen and guest bathroom make this a steal for 1 or 2. Infant bed and accessories available upon request. Access to beautiful outdoor garden with waterfall & pond, fireplace in outdoor living room.
neighborhood_overview: Madison Park is a walking, biking neighborhood with families and small children, dogs and chickens will be heard when outside of the studio. It is close to everything and one of the most desired areas in the city to live.
host_about:
My husband and I have traveled extensively to Europe, China, Mexico and across the U.S. Our favorite place to be is in our own Emerald City. We love our many chef owned restaurants, the green spaces, proximity to the City Center, the many Universities and beaches all surrounded by white snow capped mountains. Seattle has more places to eat breakfast than most major cities twice our size and we have 2 Happy Hours in Seattle. The usual afternoon/early evening and the late 10pm-1am, great after a show or concert.  We are a professional couple that enjoys reading, meeting new people, avid music fans and of course traveling. I have been a guest at many other Airbnb homes and enjoyed meeting new people and relating to a neighborhood instead of a hotel lobby. When we decided to become hosts our goal was to provide both the comfort and amenities of an upscale hotel and the feel of a home in an amazing neighborhood. We are close to everything with enough distance from the busy downtown corridor that finding a quiet park or sidewalk restaurant you can walk to from the studio lends the opportunity for a variety of memorable experiences.
        "Something for everyone" is what we tell anyone visiting Seattle. 
We look forward to welcoming you to our home for work or play!

name: Cozy & Private 2-Bedroom Home
description:
Relax with the whole family at this peaceful place to stay.
The "Little House" is centrally located near Seattle Children's Hospital and the University of Washington. Near to Lake Washington (Sandpoint, Matthews Beach Park), Meadowbrook Pond, and the Climate Pledge Arena.
A short drive to get downtown, the U District, Capital Hill, and 7.5 miles to the terminals
A large fenced yard for lounging, picnicking, or playing around. Three large blueberry bushes provide delicious blueberries seasonally.
neighborhood_overview:
Meadowbrook is a friendly neighborhood with an "urban suburban mix" feel.

There is a coffee shop as well as an Italian restaurant within walking distance.

Walk over to the Meadowbrook Pond and see all kinds of birds and even beavers.

Meadowbrook has been inhabited since the end of the last glacial period (c. 8,000 BCE—10,000 years ago). The tu-hoo-beed (Thornton Creek) hah-chu-ahbsh (Lake People) of the Duwamish (Dkhw’Duw’Absh, People of the Inside) Lushootseed (Skagit-Nisqually) Coast Salish native people where the original inhabitants.

Meadowbrook Playfield has some seriously awesome play structures!

Swim at the Meadowbrook Pool!

Recreate at the Meadowbrook Community Center!

Quite a lovely community.

host_about:
Jimi and I are super excited to be a part of the airbnb community. We have been hosting people for about three years now, and we have loved every minute of it. I (William) have lived in the Pacific Northwest for 20+ years. I know most of the great spots to experience a good bite or an amazing sunset. Jimi is originally from the Philippines and brings his amazing flair to our home. 

We started hosting people on airbnb because my father is half paralyzed.  We use the money from airbnb to help support him as he cannot support himself. So we treat every guest as the blessing they are, a helping hand to my father's better fortunes. We have recently added a few extra units to see if we can start a little boutique hotel. Even though our locations are expensive, our profits are not high. But our current goal is to get enough funds to supply a down payment to build a disability home for my father.

To that end we want all of our guests to have amazing experiences. We do whatever it takes to provide a wonderful trip, just ask and we provide. 

Thank you so much for considering our home and we look forward to meeting you on the next adventure.

name: Room#1 Seattle Spruce Street BnB
description: Enjoy easy access to everything from this perfectly located home base. Enter main door from the front porch, common room and stairs visible - 2nd floor large room w/ hardwood floor, granite table, king bed, AC & shared full bath w/ 1 other room in the Squire Park: Central District. Room & house have keyless entry.  Keyless entry instructions & code provided day of check in.  Home is split in "two", host family lives in basement and main floor. Airbnb / common room on main and 2nd floors
host_about:
About Us: Family of five, adults work online.  We have three kids and enjoy hosting and have been doing so before having kids of our own.  We are in town about 3-6 months a year and airbnb when we are in town.  We also have two fur babies that frequently join us in Seattle.  We are pretty outgoing and adventurous but work hard to provide a space that is kid free, pet free and host free for the most part!  ;)

About the house:  The home is a large, three level 1888 built home (basement, main floor and 2nd floor) with three bedrooms on the 2nd floor.  In 2017, we renovated the home to create two separate living quarters: a space to allow our guests to find privacy and a space to allow us to live on-site and host (something we really enjoy).  We airbnb the 3, 2nd floor room.  Our short renters have the main entry (front door / green / with welcome sign) and a common room with filtered water, coffee / tea, microwave, mini-fridge and seating and dish ware and dish ware service.  

The home is in the Central District / Squire Park Neighborhood.  We walk or bus from our home .. very convenient location.  Within a few blocks include: mini-markets, cafes, Whole Foods Grocery, hospitals, many tasty small local business restaurants, local breweries, library, grocery store, coffee (of course!), Walgreens and more!  

Transportation: Parking is getting challenging in our area, we encourage folks to not bring a car if planning to park all day.  We have 2 hr street parking on our street, from 7 am - 6 pm but open blocks are near us and paid parking is 3 blocks away.  Most folks get around by walking, light rail, street car, bike, Uber / Lyft or the bus.  Below are distances to main attractions. 
International District: 1.0 mi / 1.6 km(also has a light rail station)
Mt. Baker Light Rails station: 1.6 mi / 2.6 km
CenturyLink Stadium: 1.5 mi / 2.4 km
Downtown: 1.5 mi / 2.4 km
Capitol Hill (Seattle Central College): 1.5 mi / 2.4 km
Pike Place Market: 2.0 mi / 3.2 km
Space Needle: 2.5 mi / 4 km

More About Us:  We are a family of 5 with two fur babies tagging along.  The mom is a retired engineer, turned software, worldschooler and blogger.  Dad is a software engineer.  We have three kids 12, 9 and 7 who are all well traveled, inquisitive, fun small people!  We have been hosting people from all over the US and internationally  (Philippines, Australia, Turkey, Colombia, Venezuela, Brazil, Korea, Japan, China, Singapore, Taiwan, Germany, Solvania, etc. ) for about 12 years.  Mom and kids are usually out of the country (most often in Playa Negra, Costa Rica, catching waves!)

name: Lakeridge Gardens
description: Enjoy a lovely stay at a beautiful  & eclectic mid-century home overlooking Lake Washington.  Up to 2 people (no guests permitted), have access to thier own suite w/ separate entrance, stylish bathroom,  cheery kitchenette & patio overlooking the lake. You'll love waking up to heated bathroom floors & stunning lake views.  Relax after a day exploring the PNW outdoor beauty or a day-out in town in your own hot tub or sauna. Only a 20-30 min drive to Airport, DT Seattle or Bellevue.
neighborhood_overview:
The Lakeridge community is one of the hidden gems in the Seattle region. We are on the ridge overlooking Seattle, Mercer Island, Renton and Lake Washington. Its a lovely quiet neighborhood full of nice mid-century view homes with stunning gardens & views to match! It makes a terrific base to explore the area provided you have your own transportation. Lakeridge is also close to many wonderful attractions in the south end of Seattle. Very close you will find Kubata Gardens Japanese style park and Seward Park; one of Seattle's best outdoor parks and part of the Olmstead Brothers Parks legacy plan . The local Asian food & African food scene is rocking and we have many award-winning South Seattle breweries and wineries within 15 minutes drive.

Lakeridge is a residential, very safe nieghborhood full of nice single family homes. There is no transit and no shops within walking distance of our area, so the only foot traffic we get are neighbors walking thier dogs or getting daily e
host_about:
Originally from England I have been travelling the world for 50 years and really appreciate affordable, unique stays and great hospitality. I have always found that staying at locally owned, smaller places is the very best way to enjoy any town. I co-host Lakeridge Gardens with my wife Dah, from southern Thailand-(who I met while travelling!).
We share the house with our two lovely indoor/outdoor young cats & both work full-time (including on weekends). While our space is a newer listing; we are certainly not newbies when it comes to travel & hospitality and as such plan to make your stay a very memorable one. As a Seattle native for the pst 30+ years I am also very well versed and very well connected to to the town. I worked in the entertainment (music, festivals and bicycle event production) for many years and we are quite the local foodies. Our location & suite is just superb for year round stays; we have the best beaches & parks in the city right at your doorstep. We are updating our local attraction  in our local guide book weekly with great "inside" tips for our guests.  I tend to lean more towards  authentic, family run food choices that offer good value and proven good food . Do not hesitate to ask for any recommendations during your stay

neighborhood_overview: This is called the Leschi / Mt Baker neighborhood. We have access to 3 separate parks that feel like you are in the heart of a forest rather than the heart of a city.  You can find people walking their dogs or out for a quick jog at all times of the day so it's a very walk-able neighborhood. We have access to 3 bus lines, 14,4,& the 8, as well as a 5 minute bus ride to the Mt Baker Light Rail which can take you to  airport or University of Washington. I love this neighborhood. The bus driver told me the other day that this is her favorite route and calls it a hidden gem because it is so close to everything and yet has a very neighborhood feeling.

description: Discover the best of Seattle, with this one bedroom apartment in Capitol Hill. . It’ll be easy to simply show up and start living in this airy Blueground furnished apartment with its fully-equipped kitchen, stylish living room, and our dedicated, on-the-ground support. (ID #SEA598)
neighborhood_overview: This furnished apartment is situated in Capitol Hill, a diverse neighborhood known for being the center of the city’s LGBT culture and community. Packed with bars, restaurants, clubs, alternative cafes, and indie stores, this area always has something going on. There are tons of large green spaces to choose from, for instance, Volunteer Park offers walking trails, a plant conservatory as well as an Asian Art Museum and panoramic city views. To reach this neighborhood there are trolleybuses, a streetcar as well as access to the Link Light Rail.
host_about:
We’re Blueground, a global proptech company with several thousand move-in-ready apartments in a growing number of major cities around the world. With flexible terms and homes in vibrant, centrally based neighborhoods, you’ll feel at home and free to roam for as long as you want — a month, a year, or longer. 

Each apartment is thoughtfully designed with exclusive furnishings, fully equipped kitchens, and incredible amenities – making every day a five-star experience. From day one, you’ll enjoy high-speed Wi-Fi, premium linens, and smart home entertainment. Plus, access to pools, gyms, and outdoor spaces in select buildings.

Why stress over your apartment? We provide a hassle-free alternative — a consistent, quality guest experience that starts even before you arrive. Because we let you book our most up-to-date apartment listings online, confirm with a click, pay securely, and check in easily. 

Even better? You can enhance your stay with car rentals, grocery delivery, laundry services, and more through our special partnerships. 

During your stay
Upon arrival, you’ll either be greeted personally by a Blueground team member or given self-check-in instructions. The entire apartment is yours! You’ll enjoy reliable support via email, phone, and our Guest App, where you can request everything from a home cleaning to extra towels. 

We’ll share all details upon confirmation of your stay.

description:
Our beautiful little cottage features light, open, smart, peaceful design. We are in the wonderful Maple Leaf neighborhood, close to many urban amenities, but a quiet, clean respite from the hustle and bustle of the city. We are just 0.9 miles from the Northgate light rail station. We offer the perfect balance of privacy and host availability. It's ideal for 1-2 people, but can accommodate a 3rd guest.

Our City of Seattle Short-Term Rental Operator License # is: STR-OPLI-19-002418.
neighborhood_overview: People who live in the Maple Leaf neighborhood simply love it and take great pride in it.  Most homes are what might be called modest (no mansions here!) but well cared for.  It's a great walking neighborhood, with parks, restaurants, coffee shops and other businesses right at hand.  People are friendly.  It's just 8 miles to downtown, but doesn't feel like it.  There's good access to the freeway and public transportation.  Really, it feels like a small town inside a big city.

name: Heart of West Seattle / 9m drive to Alki Beach
description:
✿ Elegant room in a new modern home, located in a quiet, safe & charming neighborhood, steps away from the vibrant West Seattle Alaska Junction.
✿ We painted the walls, assembled furniture & carefully picked out every item to make a beautiful space for our guests to enjoy. It comes w high-speed wifi & free street parking.
✿ After a day of exploring nearby beaches w stunning sunsets, kayaking the Puget Sound, or eating your way through the Farmer’s Market, come home & unwind in your cozy room.
neighborhood_overview:
PRIME LOCATION — CHARMING ✣ SAFE ✣ WALK TO EVERYTHING
✿ No car, no problem! One block away from the heart of one of Seattle's best neighborhoods, close to transit, the home has a 97 walk score making it a "Walker's Paradise"
✿ 9 m drive to Alki sandy beach w/ stunning sunsets & city skyline

Restaurants, bars, coffee shops, spa, pilates/yoga/gym, live music, bike shop (rent a bike & you're at Alki Beach in 5-10 min!), and four grocery stores within 5 minutes (Safeway, QFC, Whole Foods & Trader Joe’s) and lots of cute shops at your doorstep.

During the summer, there is a Farmer’s market every Sunday, just a block away on California Ave. If you’re staying with us on a summer weekend don’t miss it. It is a wonderful opportunity to purchase delicious local treats and goods. Additionally, there is an art walk every 2nd Thursday of the month.
host_about:
Our guest rooms were made with love and care. We painted the walls, assembled furniture, and carefully picked out every item ourselves to make a beautiful space for our guests to enjoy. 

Mindfulness is our core value and we brought that practice to the whole process of setting up the rooms. We chose materials that are eco-friendly and free of harmful chemicals. We are thoughtful about our impact on our guests' health and safety, our neighbors, our environment, and the city of Seattle. 

We're looking forward to hosting you here. 

ABOUT US: 
We met in New York while attending a graduate program and bonded over our mutual passion for meditation. The lush nature and peacefulness of Seattle attracted us, so once the opportunity to move presented itself, we seized it right away.  After a drive across the country we felt at home here right away. This city is so magical and full of fond memories. 

We hope you'll have a fantastic and memorable stay with us.

name: Blue Oasis: Safe Modern room in Cap Hill Townhouse
description:
Blue Oasis is a fully furnished room in Seattle at the intersection of Cap Hill, Cherry Hill, and First Hill.

Blue Oasis is located on the first floor with a large closet and private bathroom with tub. It's furnished with a queen bed, luxury sheets, and flannel comforter. The room has fast charge USB-A, USB-C ports, multi-tone lamp, and gig speed ethernet. It faces west and even has its own patio area. The space is set up for both long and short term stays!
host_about:
Hey everyone! I'm Karim (like Abdul-Jabar). I love all things food and sports (especially futball, basketball, football). I studied Electrical and Computer Engineering in Pennsylvania and Switzerland, worked all over America for the aviation industry and big tech, and now do research and work in academia in Computer Science. 

On the personal side, I am a former semi-pro soccer player and I played for my school's club MMA team. I am on and off about dieting but when I am, I'm strict on eating kosher/halal and as much seafood as possible. 

I am a huge foodie so any tips on food or even sightseeing your city are greatly appreciated! I speak several languages (some better than others). I love to travel and learn about different cultures so I tend to click with people. I've traveled most of Western Europe, half of America, the Middle East, and Southeast Asia. On short stays, I don't like to mingle too much with my host because I am usually there just to sleep but on longer stays, I definitely like chatting!

Thank you!

name: **Private Apt - 1 Bdrm with King Bed. Min to DT!**
description:
Bright and airy guest suite in beautifully updated home nestled in a centrally located Seattle neighborhood walking distance to restaurants, bars, coffee shops, and grocery stores.

Close to downtown, Space Needle, 90 Walk Score.

Private entrance, washer dryer, full kitchen, dishwasher & 2 smart TVs. Porch and access to backyard.

Coffee and French press provided.

Brand new king bed, sofa bed, and table have been updated in the apartment.
neighborhood_overview:
We are located right on the border of Madison Park, and Capitol Hill.

Head East down our hill and you will run into Cafe Flora, delicious vegetarian cuisine. Past that, you will find the Arboretum, 230 acres of trails to tour you through myriad PNW plants - some found nowhere else in the world. Near the University of Washington you can also rent canoes and explore by water.

If you head West you can get delicous coffee and pastries at the famous Seattle Macrina Bakery, or stop for a local beer and some tacos at Rocket Taco.

Further to the west you will find some of Seattle's busiest nightlife. Have a unique cocktail at Cannon, or head down to Seattle Speakeasy, Tavern Law.
host_about:

neighborhood_overview:
The Seward Park area is a picturesque neighborhood nestled in Seattle, Washington. It's renowned for its stunning namesake, Seward Park, a lush peninsula jutting into Lake Washington. The park offers serene nature trails, a sandy beach, and remarkable viewpoints. The neighborhood itself features a mix of residential charm and green spaces, making it an inviting haven for outdoor enthusiasts and those seeking a tranquil urban escape.

Residents and visitors alike can enjoy tree-lined streets, cozy cafes, unique shops, and easy access to the beautiful Seward Park, known for its lush greenery and waterfront views. The neighborhood's rich history and diverse culinary scene make it a must-visit destination for those looking to experience the authentic spirit of Seattle.

It’ll be easy to simply show up and start living in this elegantly Blueground furnished apartment with its fully-equipped kitchen, pretty living room, and our dedicated, on-the-ground support. (ID #SEA582)
neighborhood_overview: This furnished apartment is located in First Hill, which is close to Downtown while still providing calm and privacy. There is a high concentration of high-quality hospitals here as well as impressive mansions. Along Madison Avenue, there are many dining and shopping opportunities. For culture lovers, the Frye Art Museum offers classic paintings while the Town Hall hosts concerts, book talks, and community forums. The First Hill Streetcar connects this neighborhood with Chinatown and Capitol Hill.
host_about:
We’re Blueground, a global proptech company with several thousand move-in-ready apartments in a growing number of major cities around the world. With flexible terms and homes in vibrant, centrally based neighborhoods, you’ll feel at home and free to roam for as long as you want — a month, a year, or longer. 

Each apartment is thoughtfully designed with exclusive furnishings, fully equipped kitchens, and incredible amenities – making every day a five-star experience. From day one, you’ll enjoy high-speed Wi-Fi, premium linens, and smart home entertainment. Plus, access to pools, gyms, and outdoor spaces in select buildings.

Why stress over your apartment? We provide a hassle-free alternative — a consistent, quality guest experience that starts even before you arrive. Because we let you book our most up-to-date apartment listings online, confirm with a click, pay securely, and check in easily. 

Even better? You can enhance your stay with car rentals, grocery delivery, laundry services, and more through our special partnerships. 

During your stay
Upon arrival, you’ll either be greeted personally by a Blueground team member or given self-check-in instructions. The entire apartment is yours! You’ll enjoy reliable support via email, phone, and our Guest App, where you can request everything from a home cleaning to extra towels. 

We’ll share all details upon confirmation of your stay.

name: Huge Home a Block from Green Lake
description:
This beautiful 6BR Green Lake home was fully updated in May 2017. It is 3,400 sq. ft. and features six bedrooms, two fireplaces, 2 full kitchens, comfy shared living spaces, two sofa-beds, & a large rooftop deck with great views of the lake.
We are just a short block from beautiful Green Lake, and walking distance to many great local restaurants, cafes, shops and outdoor activities, as well as a short drive (or longer walk) to the University of Washington and the Zoo.
neighborhood_overview: Seattle is among the most active cities in the U.S. and Green Lake is Seattle’s hub for recreation. Circling the lake is a 2.8 mile walking/running/wheels trail. The park also offers tennis and basketball courts, hiking trails, baseball and soccer fields, 9-iron golf course, public swimming pool and beaches, boat/kayak/paddle board rentals, and a theatre. The trail is also a great place for people watching and the best way to access many restaurants and shops lining the lake.
host_about:
I moved to Seattle from Michigan and my wife, Nadia, moved out from NYC.  We have lived in several of Seattle's neighborhoods, and chose Seattle’s Greenlake neighborhood as our favorite. 
Nadia and I have both traveled extensively, and between us we have visited over 50 countries and 6 continents.  All of this travel has allowed us to stay in hundreds of hotels, hostels, and Airbnbs, and we borrowed their best ideas for our own properties.

description:
The neighborhood of West Seattle is close to downtown, but has that relaxed beach community vibe and just 10 minutes to Alki Beach.

neighborhood_overview:
Greenwood is a quiet residential neighborhood. There is a neighborhood center less than a mile away where you'll find cozy restaurants, a couple breweries, and shops. We are also located just a quick drive/bike/or bus ride away from the fun and hip neighborhood of Ballard, which is a must visit stop in Seattle for its huge variety of restaurants, small breweries, maritime industry, entertainment, shops, museums, and to visit the Ballard Locks.

In the immediate surrounding areas you will also find commercial centers with grocery stores, pet stores, etc. There is a large grocery store and a handful of restaurants just a couple blocks away as well.

The beautiful Puget Sound and it's beaches are very close by.

Though it's rarely visited by tourists, nearby, there is also a big forested park called Carkeek Park a 10 minute walk from our house where you can take an urban hike all the way down to the waterfront where you'll find beautiful views and a beach.
host_about: I love to travel. My little dog, who found us on a Mexican beach 8 years ago, often comes with. Together him, my partner Ermanno, and I have traveled all over. We enjoy meeting new people, being active, biking in all forms, learning new things, long walks, and nature.

neighborhood_overview:
The Eastlake neighborhood in Seattle is a vibrant and eclectic area nestled along the eastern shore of Lake Union. Characterized by a blend of residential and commercial spaces, Eastlake offers a unique urban experience with a touch of tranquility.

Residential streets are lined with a mix of historic and modern homes, providing a diverse architectural landscape. Many properties offer stunning views of Lake Union, the city skyline, and the surrounding mountains, adding to the area's charm.

Eastlake Avenue, the main thoroughfare, is bustling with a variety of cafes, restaurants, and shops, catering to both locals and visitors. The neighborhood's culinary scene reflects a diverse range of cuisines, making it a haven for food enthusiasts.

description: Our beautiful 2023 townhome designed with high quality & comfort in mind.  Enjoy amazing rooftop view of Lake Union, Mt. Lively Wallingford neighborhood offers an ideal central location - easy access to all Seattle hot spots, yet away from downtown noise & safety concerns. neighborhood_overview: Wallingford is an amazing neighborhood just north of Lake Union and downtown, south of Green Lake and the Woodland Park Zoo, east of Ballard and the Locks, and west of the University of Washington. It truly is an ideal central location, accessible to all exciting hot spots and yet sheltered from the city center’s nuances and safety concerns. There is no better location to stay for your Seattle trip. Wallingford is a casual, family-friendly neighborhood that many students, families and high-tech professionals live in due to its proximity to UW and major tech employers. The heart of the University District is "The Ave" (University Way), a bustling street lined with various restaurants, cafes, shops, and bookstores. It's the perfect place to grab a coffee, savor international cuisine, or shop for unique clothing and gifts.

Green spaces are abundant in the University District. The nearby Ravenna Park offers a peaceful escape with trails for hiking and jogging. The University of Washington campus features the beautiful Drumheller Fountain and the scenic Quad, where you can relax, read, or enjoy a picnic.

When the opportunity arises I also love to travel and experience the many cultures around the world.  Recent trips have taken me to Ireland, Russia, Italy, Germany, Spain, Mexico, Cuba, Bahamas and Croatia.  As a host I hope to provide the same unique, comfortable, fun and affordable experience I have had as a guest using AirBnB.  I really enjoy sharing my house (and city) with the all of the wonderful folks who show up at my doorstep.

1. Explore Pike Place Market: This iconic market is a must-visit in Seattle. You can stroll through the bustling stalls, sample local produce, buy fresh seafood, and grab a cup of coffee at the original Starbucks.

2. Try Seattle's Famous Coffee: Speaking of coffee, Seattle is known for its thriving coffee culture. Don't miss the opportunity to try a cup of freshly brewed coffee at one of the many local cafes or visit the Starbucks Reserve Roastery for a unique coffee experience.

3. Visit the Space Needle: Head to the Space Needle, Seattle's most recognizable landmark. Take the elevator up to the observation deck for breathtaking views of the city skyline and surrounding mountains.

I am from China and have lived in the US for 16 years. I have been fortunate to build up a group of close friends who believed in me. They say I am kind, loyal, reliable, and fun to be with. I cannot imagine life without my friends. They are the foundation on which I have built my life. I am a runner and like all outdoor activities. I love to travel when I can. 各位租客大家好！我来自中国，现在在美国生活了16年。我很幸运地结交了一群信任我的好朋友，她们说我善良，忠诚，可靠，热情，开朗，有趣。我有进取的心，有似水的梦怀，有崇高的理想。  我，幽默宽容。不喜欢看别人满面怒容的样子，我认为微笑才是天下最美的风景。“比大地宽阔的是海洋，比海洋宽阔的是天空，比天空宽阔的是人的心灵。”  我，积极进取。小小的我是一粒沙，但不甘于落后，一生庸碌无为。我，爱好跑步，热爱旅行，非常喜欢户外运动，渴望把生活中的美好事物分享给身边的朋友。比起旅行，我更加喜欢去学习当地的文化，了解他们的生活。我作为房东，在我的住宿里，我一定尽我所能为您提供一切便利，使您的旅行更加轻松愉快。感谢您驻留在我这里……

host_about:
We’re Blueground, a global proptech company with several thousand move-in-ready apartments in a growing number of major cities around the world. With flexible terms and homes in vibrant, centrally based neighborhoods, you’ll feel at home and free to roam for as long as you want — a month, a year, or longer. 

Each apartment is thoughtfully designed with exclusive furnishings, fully equipped kitchens, and incredible amenities – making every day a five-star experience. From day one, you’ll enjoy high-speed Wi-Fi, premium linens, and smart home entertainment. Plus, access to pools, gyms, and outdoor spaces in select buildings.

Why stress over your apartment? We provide a hassle-free alternative — a consistent, quality guest experience that starts even before you arrive. Because we let you book our most up-to-date apartment listings online, confirm with a click, pay securely, and check in easily. 

Even better? You can enhance your stay with car rentals, grocery delivery, laundry services, and more through our special partnerships. 

During your stay
Upon arrival, you’ll either be greeted personally by a Blueground team member or given self-check-in instructions. The entire apartment is yours! You’ll enjoy reliable support via email, phone, and our Guest App, where you can request everything from a home cleaning to extra towels. 

We’ll share all details upon confirmation of your stay.

https://www.argosycruises.com/christmas-ship-festival-schedule/
neighborhood_overview:
Join this unique friendly lake union live aboard community of floating homes, house boats and house barges. Lake Union is a freshwater lake in Seattle, joined by waterways to Puget Sound and Lake Washington. Gas Works Park is our backyard. The park sits on the north end of the lake, a 19.1 acre public park built on the site of a former gasification plant, with ruins and pieces of the old plant still standing and built into the park. The park offers grassy hills for kite flying, picnics, and wide vistas of the lake and city. The Burke-Gilman Trail runs along the northern edge of the park.
Seaplanes scoot in and out of Lake Union, on their way to and from the San Juan Islands and British Columbia. The lake shores are lined with houseboats, and commercial and private docks for owners and renters of tugs, yachts, tour ships, sailboats, kayaks and canoes. The Center for Wooden Boats is a nautical museum on the south shore, with historical boats, sailing events, classes and workshops.
host_about:
Amelia & Suzi~Daughter & Mom Team~Best Friends~We are true Seattlites at heart!  We LOVE our city, live in the most beautiful areas in Seattle at Lake Union, Greenlake, & Ballard.  We are born and raised here in the Pacific Northwest.  We love the water, the nearby islands (Lopez & Vashon & all of the San Juans), the mountains, the fresh ocean air, running around Greenlake, swimming at the Greenlake pool, biking on the Ship Canal Trail, First Thursday Adventure Runs, Core power hot yoga, biking the Burke Gilman trail and through out the city...gazing at the snow capped mountains.  Seattle is a beautiful place to explore!

As your hosts, we love to assist in anyway that will make your trip the best.  We have private homes, floating homes and private Master bedrooms in shared homes.  We are social, friendly and super handy to assist with your trip if you reach out to us.  Otherwise, we provide the things you need and a custom binder of our area insights to set you on your way to a great visit in Seattle.

neighborhood_overview:
The neighborhood...
On a map, it looks like the building is adjacent to the freeway, but freeways run under the city near the building, making it easier to walk the downtown neighborhood than it looks on a map.

Downtown is the main business area, waterfront, Pike Place Market, and Seattle's primary shopping district. Downtown is compact compared to other West Coast cities, so it's easy to walk everywhere. The western part of First Hill, where you'd be staying, is a wonderful, prime, sub-neighborhood within Downtown.

We're a block east of the Central Business District that includes the Convention Center, a 7-minute walk from the Westlake Light rail link to/from the airport, a block south of the Pike/Pine Corridor which encompasses the retail shopping core, and a block west of Capitol Hill, Seattle's popular district for nightlife and entertainment. This location has a walk score of 98 and a transit score of 100, so it's easy to get anywhere from here.

neighborhood_overview:
Capitol Hill is Seattle's most vibrant and exciting neighborhood. It is the home of people from all walks of life - from artists to politicians to immigrants and professionals. It is the home of a major Catholic cathedral, universities/colleges, and the center of gay and lesbian activism.
Farmers markets, French bakeries, museums, gourmet restaurants, never ending nightlife, and historic monuments, active and beautiful parks make this the most walk-able, cultural and diverse area in all of Seattle.
In the midst of this urban oasis is a peaceful and convenient, fully remodeled home, in a century old house built 1902. Capitol Hill is a great destination for a business assignment, traveling adventures, or a vacationing family.

To access other parts of the city from here, simply hop on the streetcar.

neighborhood_overview:
Proudly named for the neighboring nationally renowned University of Washington, this house is located only a quarter mile from campus. Check out the Suzzallo library at the university for the closest thing to Harry Potter’s Hogwarts or if you are lucky enough to visit in the Spring take a post-worthy photo among the cherry blossoms of the main campus square.

This student neighborhood is always bustling with activity. You'll find an abundance of budget-friendly international restaurants, coffee shops, bookshops, and music venues just blocks away.

Please remember this neighborhood where the University and student housing are located so there may be the occasional weekend party, especially in the spring season. Feel free to join in the fun or make use of the provided earplugs, but if absolute silence is a necessity you may want to seek other accommodations.

name: Seattle Urban Village- O-private room
description: Heart of Eastlake Urban Village, come enjoy the characters and the history of our neighborhood: your own private room in the original historic landmark home to Seattle's lumber industry pioneer. This fun space in Seattle is the perfect quaint getaway only minutes from all the excitement of everything Seattle has to offer, and walking distance to beautiful Lake Union and Capital Hill. Make yourself at home- enjoy a fully equiped kitchen, TV, and Wif
neighborhood_overview: With Amazon headquarters nearby, this neighborhood is vibrant and hi tech.  We are close to Unviersity of Washington, biotech hub of Lake Union.  There are lots of ways to get out and enjoy Lake Union here. There is a boat launch for kayaks and canoes, or you can join the Lake Union Crew squad. Many small parks dot the shore, including Fairview Park and Eastlake Bouledrome, which claims to have the best waterfront bocce ball in Seattle (though we can’t imagine there’s much competition for that title). It’s always fun to grab a table on the deck at one of the restaurants along the lake (like Eastlake Bar and Grill or Serafina) so you can watch the boats and seaplanes. If you’ve got the time, you can go on your very own seaplane ride and get a great view of Seattle, and Eastlake of course!

Welcome to our property!  I am a lawyer and property manager.  My husband and I lead a small team to help make your stay as easy as possible.

host_about:
I am an artist and a maker (metalsmith cum interior designer/ permaculture landscape architect.) When you stay with me you may see projects in motion, functional art, experiments in off-grid heating and some creative detritus which lingers from all of THIS. Your experience with me will not be sanitary and spotless, but rather colorful and memorable.  I will go out of my way to make sure you get your needs met, and sometimes hyper-focus on things you probably would otherwise not care about during your stay. Sometimes there will be clutter. But if you need a specialty car seat or other rare object, I will go out of my way to manifest it.

My passion and personal challenge is to anticipate the needs of my guest before they even anticipate their own desires. (extra towels, airport pick up, dairy allergy, baby monitor because you are sleep training with Ferber method while traveling, but also want a cocktail while doing so, etc.) You may find me overly communicative in non-linear ways. Its due to my OCD and excitement at hopefully making your stay memorable.

neighborhood_overview:
At four square miles, Seattle's Central District (also known as "the CD") is the city's oldest surviving residential area and is now one of the most interesting and diverse neighborhoods in the city.

The CD was once home to Jimi Hendrix, Ernestine Anderson, Kenny G, and Quincy Jones. And the Central District is – no surprise – centrally located. Residents of the neighborhood describe the neighborhood as "diverse, central, bike-friendly, residential, interesting, and walkable."

The CD has a number of designated historical landmarks:

- Immaculate Conception Church, 820 18th Avenue (1904)
- - Old Firehouse #23, CAMP, 722 18th Avenue (1909)
- Victorian House, 1414 S. Washington Street (1900)
- Langston Hughes Cultural Arts Center (formerly Bikur Cholim Synagogue) 104 17th Avenue (1912)
- 23rd Avenue Houses Group, 812-828 23rd Avenue (1892-93)
- James Washington Jr. Home and Studio, 1816 26th Avenue (1918)
- First African Metho

host_about:
Hello,   

I have lived in Seattle for 9 years.  Belltown, Seattle is home.   I take pride in sharing this wonderful part of the world, and its unique and diverse culture.  I also have rental homes in my favorite vacation spots of Long Beach, WA, Panama City Beach, FL, and Clermont-Orlando, FL. My goal is to provide you with hospitality that is enjoyable and memorable that celebrates the best of each location.  You will enjoy  comfortable, clean, classic, modern,  quality, updated designer accommodations that are inspired by nature and the essence of each location.

I look forward to hosting you!

Carlos A.
